e a [[dare]]; the moment someone challenged his courage, he had to prove himself.", "kor": "도전/담력 시험", "eng": "a challenge to prove courage"}, {"page": "14", "word": "wore him down", "sentence": "She [[wore him down]] with constant begging until, exhausted, he finally gave in and said yes.", "kor": "지치게 하다/결국 설득하다", "eng": "gradually persuaded him"}, {"page": "14", "word": "reckoned", "sentence": "\"I [[reckoned]] you'd be late,\" he drawled, \"so I figured I'd wait here and rest a spell.\"", "kor": "생각하다/추측하다", "eng": "supposed; figured (dialect)"}, {"page": "14", "word": "homemade hinge", "sentence": "The little gate swung on a [[homemade hinge]], a rough metal joint that someone had hammered together by hand.", "kor": "집에서 만든 경첩", "eng": "a hand-made door hinge"}, {"page": "14", "word": "gouges", "sentence": "The knife [[gouges]] deep grooves in the soft wood, scooping out long curls with every stroke.", "kor": "[가우지스] 도려내다/파내다", "eng": "to dig or scoop out"}, {"page": "14", "word": "patiently", "sentence": "[[Patiently]], without the least sign of hurry or temper, she explained the lesson for a fourth time.", "kor": "참을성 있게/끈질기게", "eng": "with steady persistence"}, {"page": "14", "word": "once and for all", "sentence": "He wanted to settle the question [[once and for all]], finally and completely, so that it need never be argued again.", "kor": "아예 확실하게", "eng": "finally and completely"}, {"page": "14", "word": "dared", "sentence": "Jem [[dared]] Dill to touch the house, challenging him to march right up and lay a hand on the wall.", "kor": "도전하다/부추기다", "eng": "challenged (someone) to do something"}, {"page": "14", "word": "become of", "sentence": "\"Whatever will [[become of]] that poor child,\" she wondered, \"if no one ever takes him in?\"", "kor": "~이 어떻게 될까", "eng": "to happen to (someone)"}, {"page": "14", "word": "sense of responsibility", "sentence": "A strong [[sense of responsibility]] kept him at his post; he simply could not abandon a duty once it wa