", "word": "drown myself in Barker's Eddy", "sentence": "\"I'd [[drown myself in Barker's Eddy]],\" I decided dramatically — a child's wild revenge fantasy.", "kor": "바커스 에디에서 익사하다 - 협박성 공상", "eng": "a child's dramatic revenge fantasy"}, {"page": "27", "word": "advise", "sentence": "I would [[advise]] Atticus of her crimes, formally reporting to him everything she had done.", "kor": "알리다/보고하다", "eng": "to inform (formal)"}, {"page": "27", "word": "iniquities", "sentence": "I listed Calpurnia's [[iniquities]], every unjust and wicked thing she had done to me.", "kor": "[인이쿼티] 불의/부당한 행동들", "eng": "wicked, unjust acts"}, {"page": "27", "word": "solitary sprint", "sentence": "I made the [[solitary sprint]] home, a run taken all alone after the others had gone.", "kor": "혼자 달리는 것", "eng": "a run made all alone"}, {"page": "27", "word": "concluded", "sentence": "After much thought I [[concluded]] that revenge was best, deciding firmly on my plan.", "kor": "결론 내리다", "eng": "decided after thinking it over"}, {"page": "27", "word": "lose no time in", "sentence": "Atticus would [[lose no time in]] firing her, doing it the very instant I told him.", "kor": "지체하지 않고 ~하다", "eng": "to do something immediately"}, {"page": "27", "word": "packing her off", "sentence": "He would waste no time [[packing her off]], sending her away quickly and for good — or so I hoped.", "kor": "쫓아버리다/내보내다", "eng": "sending her away briskly"}, {"page": "27", "word": "worry her", "sentence": "\"Don't [[worry her]],\" Atticus said gently, telling me not to pester or trouble Calpurnia.", "kor": "걱정 끼치다/골치를 썩이다", "eng": "to pester or trouble her"}, {"page": "27", "word": "flinty", "sentence": "His voice turned [[flinty]], hard and unyielding as a piece of stone.", "kor": "단호한/돌처럼 굳은", "eng": "hard and unyielding, like flint stone"}, {"page": "27", "word": "getting rid of", "sentence": "There was no question of [[getting rid of]] Calpurnia; he would never dismiss her.", "kor": "없애다/내보내다", "eng": "removing; 