id — to see the matter exactly as he sees it.", "kor": "그의 관점에서 생각해보다", "eng": "see things exactly as he sees them"}, {"page": "32", "word": "put ourselves in her shoes", "sentence": "\"We should [[put ourselves in her shoes]],\" he said — imagine ourselves in her position.", "kor": "그녀의 입장이 되어보다", "eng": "imagine being in her position"}, {"page": "32", "word": "honest mistake", "sentence": "It was an [[honest mistake]], an error made with no bad intent at all.", "kor": "진심 어린 실수/악의 없는 실수", "eng": "an error made in good faith"}, {"page": "32", "word": "hold her responsible", "sentence": "\"You can't [[hold her responsible]] for it,\" he said — you can't lay the blame on her.", "kor": "그녀를 책임지게 하다", "eng": "to blame her for it"}, {"page": "32", "word": "bursting with", "sentence": "She came home [[bursting with]] news, so full of it she could hardly hold it in.", "kor": "~으로 터질 것 같은/가득 찬", "eng": "overflowing with"}, {"page": "32", "word": "bend the law", "sentence": "\"Sometimes folks ask us to [[bend the law]],\" he said — to stretch the rules a little in their favour.", "kor": "법을 약간 구부리다/융통성 있게 적용하다", "eng": "to apply the law flexibly"}, {"page": "32", "word": "remains rigid", "sentence": "But the law [[remains rigid]], staying strict and unbending no matter who asks.", "kor": "엄격하게 유지되다", "eng": "stays strictly unchanged"}, {"page": "32", "word": "disgrace", "sentence": "It would be a [[disgrace]] to the family, a shame they would never live down.", "kor": "수치/망신", "eng": "shame; dishonour"}, {"page": "32", "word": "three generations", "sentence": "The land had stayed in the family for [[three generations]], passing from grandfather to father to son.", "kor": "삼 대에 걸쳐", "eng": "through three generations"}, {"page": "32", "word": "honest day's work", "sentence": "He had never done an [[honest day's work]] in his life — a full, fair day of honest labour.", "kor": "정직한 하루의 일", "eng": "a full day of honest labour"}, {"page": "32", "word": "recollection", "sentence": "To the best of his [[recollection]], as far back as he could remember, it had always been so.", "kor": "기억/회상", "eng": "memory; what one remembers"}, {"page": "32", "word": "animals", "sentence": "The Ewells lived like [[animals]], wild and lawless, with no manners or rules.", "kor": "동물", "eng": "wild creatures (here, of the Ewells)"}, {"page": "32", "word": "faintest symptom", "sentence": "There wasn't the [[faintest symptom]] of conscience in him, not the smallest sign of one.", "kor": "가장 미미한 징후", "eng": "the slightest sign"}, {"page": "32", "word": "force", "sentence": "\"You can't [[force]] them to come,\" he said — you can't make them by sheer compulsion.", "kor": "강제로", "eng": "to compel by force"}, {"page": "32", "word": "silly", "sentence": "It would be [[silly]] to fine a starving family, a foolish and pointless thing to do.", "kor": "어리석은/바보 같은", "eng": "foolish; pointless"}, {"page": "32", "word": "new environment", "sentence": "The boy couldn't bear a [[new environment]], the strange and unfamiliar surroundings of a school.", "kor": "새로운 환경", "eng": "unfamiliar surroundings"}, {"page": "32", "word": "dryly", "sentence": "\"Probably,\" Atticus said [[dryly]], in a flat, faintly ironic tone.", "kor": "건조하게/담담하게", "eng": "in a flat, ironic tone"}, {"page": "32", "word": "common folk", "sentence": "\"[[Common folk]] follow the rules,\" he said — ordinary, decent people obey the law.", "kor": "평범한 사람들/일반 시민", "eng": "ordinary people"}, {"page": "32", "word": "obey the law", "sentence": "Most people [[obey the law]], doing as the rules require without ever being forced.", "kor": "법을 따르다", "eng": "to follow the law"}, {"page": "32", "word": "exclusive society", "sentence": "The Ewells belonged to an [[exclusive society]] of their own — a closed little club no one else could join.", "kor": "배타적인 집단", "eng": "a closed, members-only group (ironic)"}, {"page": "32", "word": "judiciously", "sentence": "The town looked the other way [[judiciously]], wisely and with careful judgment.", "kor": "[쥬디시어슬리] 신중하게/사려 깊게", "eng": "wisely; with careful judgment"}, {"page": "32", "word": "privileges", "sentence": "The Ewells enjoyed certain [[privileges]], special allowances granted to no one else.", "kor": "특권", "eng": "special rights or advantages"}, {"page": "32", "word": "blind to", "sentence": "The authorities stayed [[blind to]] their hunting, deliberately ignoring whatever they did.", "kor": "~에 눈을 감다/못 본 체하다", "eng": "deliberately ignoring"}, {"page": "32", "word": "permitted to", "sentence": "They were [[permitted to]] hunt year-round, allowed to do what others could not.", "kor": "허락을 받다", "eng": "allowed to"}, {"page": "32", "word": "hunt and trap out of season", "sentence": "They could [[hunt and trap out of season]], catching game even when the law forbade it.", "kor": "계절 외에 사냥하고 덫을 놓다", "eng": "hunt outside the legal season"}, {"page": "32", "word": "misdemeanor", "sentence": "For anyone else that was a [[misdemeanor]], a small, punishable offence.", "kor": "[미스디미너] 경범죄", "eng": "a minor crime"}, {"page": "32", "word": "capital felony", "sentence": "Atticus joked it was no [[capital felony]], not the gravest of all crimes — just a small thing.", "kor": "중대 범죄", "eng": "the gravest class of crime (hyperbole here)"}, {"page": "32", "word": "populace", "sentence": "The whole [[populace]] knew the Ewells, every ordinary citizen in the county.", "kor": "대중/민중", "eng": "the ordinary people; the public"}, {"page": "32", "word": "relief checks", "sentence": "They lived on [[relief checks]], the government welfare payments handed to the needy.", "kor": "구호 수표/정부 보조금", "eng": "government welfare payments"}, {"page": "32", "word": "green whiskey", "sentence": "He drank cheap [[green whiskey]], raw, half-made liquor that burned all the way down.", "kor": "덜 숙성된 위스키/저질 위스키", "eng": "raw, cheap, badly-made whiskey"}, {"page": "33", "word": "crying from hunger pains", "sentence": "The children were [[crying from hunger pains]], weeping with the ache of empty stomachs.", "kor": "배고픔으로 울다", "eng": "weeping from the pain of hunger"}, {"page": "33", "word": "landowner", "sentence": "The [[landowner]] let them hunt on his property, the man who owned the fields and woods.", "kor": "토지 소유자", "eng": "a person who owns land"}, {"page": "33", "word": "begrudges", "sentence": "No one [[begrudges]] them a few rabbits, none resents letting them take that little.", "kor": "인색하게 굴다/아까워하다", "eng": "resents giving; gives unwillingly"}, {"page": "33", "word": "game", "sentence": "They lived off the [[game]] in the woods, the wild animals they hunted for the pot.", "kor": "사냥감", "eng": "wild animals hunted for food"}, {"page": "33", "word": "change his ways", "sentence": "Mr. Ewell would never [[change his ways]], never reform or mend his behaviour.", "kor": "자신의 방식을 바꾸다", "eng": "reform his behaviour"}, {"page": "33", "word": "take out your disapproval", "sentence": "\"Don't [[take out your disapproval]] on the children,\" he said — don't vent your anger on them.", "kor": "불만을 쏟아내다", "eng": "to vent your anger (on someone)"}, {"page": "33", "word": "murmured", "sentence": "\"Yes, sir,\" I [[murmured]] — the answer barely above a whisper.", "kor": "중얼거리다", "eng": "said very quietly"}, {"page": "33", "word": "final stand", "sentence": "She made one [[final stand]], a last stubborn attempt to get her way.", "kor": "마지막 주장/버팀", "eng": "a last attempt at resistance"}, {"page": "33", "word": "bothering", "sentence": "Something was [[bothering]] her, a worry quietly gnawing at the back of her mind.", "kor": "괴롭히다/신경 쓰이게 하다", "eng": "troubling; weighing on the mind"}, {"page": "33", "word": "compromise", "sentence": "They reached a [[compromise]], a middle deal where each side gave up a little.", "kor": "타협/절충안", "eng": "an agreement by mutual give-and-take"}, {"page": "33", "word": "mutual concessions", "sentence": "It rested on [[mutual concessions]], with both sides giving way to meet halfway.", "kor": "상호 양보", "eng": "giving way on both sides"}, {"page": "33", "word": "concede", "sentence": "She would [[concede]] the point, giving in and admitting that he was right.", "kor": "양보하다/인정하다", "eng": "to yield or admit (a point)"}, {"page": "33", "word": "necessity", "sentence": "He saw the [[necessity]] of it, recognizing that it simply had to be done.", "kor": "필요성", "eng": "the state of being necessary"}, {"page": "33", "word": "bargain", "sentence": "They struck a [[bargain]]: she would go to school if he kept reading to her — a fair deal.", "kor": "거래/협상", "eng": "a deal; an agreement"}, {"page": "33", "word": "sealed without the usual formality", "sentence": "The deal was [[sealed without the usual formality]], agreed without the customary spit-and-handshake.", "kor": "일반적인 격식(침 뱉기) 없이 맺어진", "eng": "agreed without the spit-in-palm ritual"}, {"page": "33", "word": "preparing to spit", "sentence": "Scout was [[preparing to spit]], getting ready to seal the deal in the old country way.", "kor": "침 뱉을 준비를 하다 - 구두 계약의 관습", "eng": "getting ready to seal the deal Southern-style"}, {"page": "33", "word": "received with considerable disapprobation", "sentence": "Her spitting was [[received with considerable disapprobation]], met with much frowning official disapproval.", "kor": "[디스애프로베이션] 상당한 불승인을 받다/크게 반대받다", "eng": "met with strong official disapproval (mock-legal)"}, {"page": "33", "word": "learned authorities", "sentence": "The [[learned authorities]] decided otherwise — the educated grown-ups in charge (said dryly).", "kor": "더 많이 배운 당국자들/교육받은 권위자들", "eng": "the educated officials (ironic)"}, {"page": "33", "word": "accustomed to", "sentence": "She was [[accustomed to]] his big words, well used to his lawyer's way of talking.", "kor": "~에 익숙한", "eng": "used to; familiar with"}, {"page": "33", "word": "last-will-and-testament diction", "sentence": "He spoke in [[last-will-and-testament diction]], the stiff, formal wording of a legal document.", "kor": "유언장 같은 말투/격식체 표현", "eng": "lawyer-like, formal wording"}, {"page": "33", "word": "interrupt", "sentence": "I didn't dare [[interrupt]], to break in while he was still speaking.", "kor": "끼어들다/중단시키다", "eng": "to break in on someone speaking"}, {"page": "33", "word": "translation", "sentence": "Jem offered a [[translation]], putting Atticus's fancy words into plainer ones.", "kor": "번역/해석", "eng": "putting something into plainer words"}, {"page": "33", "word": "beyond our understanding", "sentence": "His meaning was [[beyond our understanding]], too difficult for children to grasp.", "kor": "이해의 범위를 넘어서는", "eng": "too hard for us to understand"}, {"page": "33", "word": "get after me", "sentence": "If I skipped school, the truant lady would [[get after me]], chasing and nagging me to go.", "kor": "나를 쫓아다니다/못살게 굴다", "eng": "to nag or pursue me"}, {"page": "33", "word": "in fits", "sentence": "His joke had us [[in fits]], laughing so hard we could barely breathe.", "kor": "웃음을 참지 못하게 하다/까르르 웃게 하다", "eng": "laughing uncontrollably"}, {"page": "33", "word": "gravely", "sentence": "He nodded [[gravely]], with a mock-serious, solemn air.", "kor": "진지하게/엄숙하게", "eng": "with mock seriousness"}, {"page": "33", "word": "flagpole", "sentence": "He shinnied up the [[flagpole]], the tall pole where the flag was raised each morning.", "kor": "깃대", "eng": "a tall pole for flying a flag"}, {"page": "33", "word": "discernible reason", "sentence": "There was no [[discernible reason]] for it, no cause that anyone could make out.", "kor": "알아볼 수 있는 이유/뚜렷한 이유", "eng": "any reason that can be made out"}, {"page": "33", "word": "aloft", "sentence": "He stayed [[aloft]] all afternoon, perched high up where no one could reach him.", "kor": "높이/위에", "eng": "high up; overhead"}, {"page": "33", "word": "remained overnight", "sentence": "He even [[remained overnight]], staying up there straight through till morning.", "kor": "밤새 머물다", "eng": "stayed through the night"}, {"page": "33", "word": "severed his supply lines", "sentence": "They [[severed his supply lines]], cutting off his food and reinforcements like an army under siege.", "kor": "[쎄벌ㄷ] 보급선을 차단하다 - 군사 용어를 유머러스하게 사용", "eng": "cut off his supplies (military humour)"}, {"page": "33", "word": "errands", "sentence": "Younger children ran [[errands]] for him, little tasks like fetching and carrying.", "kor": "[에런ㅈ] 심부름", "eng": "small tasks done for someone else"}, {"page": "33", "word": "literature", "sentence": "They smuggled him [[literature]], reading matter to pass the long hours (said with a wink).", "kor": "읽을 것", "eng": "reading material (humorous here)"}, {"page": "33", "word": "nourishment", "sentence": "And they sent up [[nourishment]] too, food to keep him going while he held out.", "kor": "영양/먹을 것", "eng": "food; sustenance"}], "4": [{"page": "34", "word": "remainder", "sentence": "She read the [[remainder]] of the chapter, finishing what was left after the others gave up.", "kor": "나머지", "eng": "the rest; what is left"}, {"page": "34", "word": "auspicious", "sentence": "It was an [[auspicious]] start to the year, a bright, promising beginning that boded well.", "kor": "상서로운/좋은 징조의", "eng": "promising success; favourable"}, {"page": "34", "word": "Project", "sentence": "Their first [[Project]] of the year, a hands-on unit of study, was all about Egypt.", "kor": "프로젝트 - 당시 진보적 교육의 학습 단위", "eng": "a progressive-education unit of work"}, {"page": "34", "word": "Unit", "sentence": "They spent a whole [[Unit]] on weather, weeks of lessons all on that single topic.", "kor": "단원/유닛", "eng": "a block of lessons on one topic"}, {"page": "34", "word": "construction paper", "sentence": "She cut shapes from bright [[construction paper]], the thick coloured sheets used for crafts.", "kor": "공작용 색지", "eng": "thick coloured paper for crafts"}, {"page": "34", "word": "wax crayon", "sentence": "He coloured the map with a [[wax crayon]], the fat waxy stick smudging under his thumb.", "kor": "밀랍 크레용", "eng": "a wax drawing crayon"}, {"pag