.", "kor": "남성용 작업복", "eng": "a man's one-piece work garment"}, {"page": "43", "word": "five o'clock bath", "sentence": "After her [[five o'clock bath]], her regular evening wash, she changed completely.", "kor": "5시 목욕", "eng": "her regular five o'clock bath"}, {"page": "43", "word": "reign over", "sentence": "By evening she would [[reign over]] the street, ruling the porch like a queen on her throne.", "kor": "군림하다/지배하다", "eng": "to rule over like a queen"}, {"page": "43", "word": "magisterial beauty", "sentence": "She had a [[magisterial beauty]], a dignified, commanding loveliness that awed us.", "kor": "위엄 있는 아름다움", "eng": "dignified, commanding beauty"}, {"page": "44", "word": "grew in God's earth", "sentence": "She loved everything that [[grew in God's earth]], every green thing that sprang from the soil.", "kor": "하나님의 땅에서 자라는", "eng": "everything growing on God's earth"}, {"page": "44", "word": "nut grass", "sentence": "She waged war on [[nut grass]], the stubborn weed that crept through her beds.", "kor": "향부자/잡초의 일종", "eng": "a stubborn invasive weed"}, {"page": "44", "word": "Second Battle of the Marne", "sentence": "One sprig, she said, was as bad as the [[Second Battle of the Marne]], a vast and terrible battle of the Great War.", "kor": "마른 제2차 전투 - 1차 세계대전의 격렬한 전투", "eng": "a vast 1918 battle of World War I"}, {"page": "44", "word": "swooped down upon", "sentence": "She [[swooped down upon]] the weed, diving at it like a hawk on its prey.", "kor": "급습하다/달려들다", "eng": "dived down upon like a hawk"}, {"page": "44", "word": "tin tub", "sentence": "She filled a [[tin tub]], the dented metal washtub, with poison.", "kor": "양철 통", "eng": "a metal washtub"}, {"page": "44", "word": "subjected it to", "sentence": "She [[subjected it to]] a chemical bath, exposing the weed to her deadly mixture.", "kor": "~에게 가하다/~을 받게 하다", "eng": "exposed it to; treated it with"}, {"page": "44", "word": "blasts", "sentence": "She killed it with [[blasts]] of poison, powerful jets sprayed straight at the root.", "kor": "강한 분사/폭발", "eng": "powerful jets or bursts"}, {"page": "44", "word": "poisonous substance", "sentence": "It was a [[poisonous substance]], a toxic brew that no plant could survive.", "kor": "독성 물질", "eng": "a toxic chemical"}, {"page": "44", "word": "stand out of the way", "sentence": "She told us to [[stand out of the way]], to step well aside out of danger.", "kor": "비켜서다/피하다", "eng": "step aside out of danger"}, {"page": "44", "word": "pull it up", "sentence": "\"Don't ever just [[pull it up]],\" she warned — yanking it out only spread it further.", "kor": "뽑아버리다", "eng": "to yank it out of the ground"}, {"page": "44", "word": "prolonged campaign", "sentence": "Killing it took a [[prolonged campaign]], a long, drawn-out battle waged over weeks.", "kor": "오랜 전투/장기간의 싸움", "eng": "a long, drawn-out military operation"}, {"page": "44", "word": "limp", "sentence": "If a sprig hung [[limp]] and drooping, lifeless and soft, the poison had won.", "kor": "축 늘어진/힘없는", "eng": "drooping; without stiffness"}, {"page": "44", "word": "sprout", "sentence": "Each new [[sprout]], every tender young shoot, had to be hunted down.", "kor": "새싹/어린 싹", "eng": "a new young shoot"}, {"page": "44", "word": "squeezed", "sentence": "She [[squeezed]] the stalk hard, pressing it tight between her fingers.", "kor": "짜다/누르다", "eng": "pressed hard between fingers"}, {"page": "44", "word": "stalk", "sentence": "She pinched the green [[stalk]], the thin stem holding up the leaves.", "kor": "줄기", "eng": "the stem of a plant"}, {"page": "44", "word": "Microscopic", "sentence": "[[Microscopic]] grains spilled out, particles so tiny no eye could ever see them.", "kor": "현미경으로 볼 수 있는/아주 작은", "eng": "too small to see without a microscope"}, {"page": "44", "word": "grains", "sentence": "Tiny [[grains]] of seed scattered, the little specks that would sprout a hundred more weeds.", "kor": "알갱이들", "eng": "tiny particles; seeds"}, {"page": "44", "word": "oozed out", "sentence": "A drop of sap [[oozed out]], leaking slowly from the broken stem.", "kor": "스며 나오다/흘러나오다", "eng": "leaked out slowly"}, {"page": "44", "word": "sprig", "sentence": "A single [[sprig]] of it, one small green shoot, could ruin a whole bed.", "kor": "작은 가지/새순", "eng": "a small shoot or twig"}, {"page": "44", "word": "dries up", "sentence": "Left in the sun it [[dries up]], shrivelling until every bit of moisture is gone.", "kor": "말라버리다", "eng": "withers; loses all moisture"}, {"page": "44", "word": "likened", "sentence": "She [[likened]] the weed to a plague, comparing it solemnly as if quoting Scripture.", "kor": "[라이큰ㄷ] 비유하다", "eng": "compared (formal, Biblical)"}, {"page": "44", "word": "such an occurrence unto", "sentence": "She compared [[such an occurrence unto]] a biblical disaster — likening the event to one, in old-fashioned speech.", "kor": "그런 일을 ~에 비유하다", "eng": "compared such an event to (archaic)"}, {"page": "44", "word": "Old Testament pestilence", "sentence": "It spread like an [[Old Testament pestilence]], a deadly plague straight out of the Bible.", "kor": "[페스털런ㅅ] 구약 성경의 역병/전염병", "eng": "a plague out of the Old Testament"}, {"page": "44", "word": "speech", "sentence": "Her [[speech]] was unusual, a way of talking unlike anyone else's in town.", "kor": "말투/언어", "eng": "way of speaking"}, {"page": "44", "word": "crisp", "sentence": "Her words were [[crisp]], brisk and clear-cut, never wasting a syllable.", "kor": "명료한/간결한", "eng": "brisk and clear-cut"}, {"page": "44", "word": "inhabitant", "sentence": "She was the oldest [[inhabitant]] of the street, the person who had lived there longest.", "kor": "주민", "eng": "a person who lives in a place"}, {"page": "44", "word": "called us by all our names", "sentence": "She [[called us by all our names]], using every single one in full when she scolded.", "kor": "우리를 모두 이름으로 부르다", "eng": "used every one of our names"}, {"page": "44", "word": "minute", "sentence": "She wore [[minute]] earrings, tiny ones almost too small to see.", "kor": "아주 작은", "eng": "extremely small"}, {"page": "44", "word": "gold prongs", "sentence": "Two [[gold prongs]] held the stones, little golden clasps gripping each gem.", "kor": "금색 걸쇠/금색 갈고리", "eng": "small gold clasps"}, {"page": "44", "word": "clipped to", "sentence": "The earrings were [[clipped to]] her ears, fastened on with small clips.", "kor": "집게로 고정된", "eng": "fastened with clips to"}, {"page": "44", "word": "eyeteeth", "sentence": "When she smiled, her [[eyeteeth]] showed, the pointed canine teeth on either side.", "kor": "송곳니/견치", "eng": "the pointed canine teeth"}, {"page": "44", "word": "admired", "sentence": "We openly [[admired]] her gold caps, gazing at them with frank longing.", "kor": "감탄하다/탐내다", "eng": "gazed at with longing"}, {"page": "44", "word": "click of her tongue", "sentence": "With a [[click of her tongue]], a small disapproving tut, she set us straight.", "kor": "혀를 차는 소리와 함께", "eng": "with a disapproving tongue-click"}, {"page": "44", "word": "thrust out", "sentence": "She [[thrust out]] her bridgework, pushing the false teeth forward to show us.", "kor": "밀어내다/내밀다", "eng": "pushed outward"}, {"page": "44", "word": "bridgework", "sentence": "She had fine [[bridgework]], a dental piece bridging the gap where teeth were missing.", "kor": "치아 교정물/브리지", "eng": "dental work bridging missing teeth"}, {"page": "44", "word": "gesture of cordiality", "sentence": "It was a [[gesture of cordiality]], a friendly little act meant to charm us.", "kor": "[코얼디알리티] 친근함의 몸짓", "eng": "a gesture of warm friendliness"}, {"page": "44", "word": "cemented", "sentence": "That sealed and [[cemented]] our friendship, making it firm and solid.", "kor": "굳히다/확고히 하다", "eng": "made firm; sealed"}, {"page": "44", "word": "benevolence", "sentence": "Her [[benevolence]] knew no bounds, her kindness and goodwill toward everyone.", "kor": "[베네볼런스] 자비로움/친절함", "eng": "kindness; goodwill"}, {"page": "44", "word": "extended to", "sentence": "Her kindness [[extended to]] the whole street, reaching as far as every house on it.", "kor": "~에까지 미치다", "eng": "reached as far as"}, {"page": "44", "word": "paused in", "sentence": "She [[paused in]] her gardening, stopping her work for a moment to talk.", "kor": "~을 잠시 멈추다", "eng": "stopped briefly in"}, {"page": "44", "word": "pursuits", "sentence": "She returned to her [[pursuits]], the gardening and chores that filled her days.", "kor": "활동들/추구하는 것들", "eng": "activities; occupations"}, {"page": "44", "word": "reaped the benefits of", "sentence": "We [[reaped the benefits of]] her good nature, enjoying all the rewards of her kindness.", "kor": "~의 혜택을 누리다", "eng": "enjoyed the rewards of"}, {"page": "44", "word": "hitherto", "sentence": "She told us things [[hitherto]] unknown, facts that until then had been hidden.", "kor": "[히덜투] 지금까지/이전에는", "eng": "until now (formal)"}, {"page": "44", "word": "hidden from", "sentence": "Secrets long [[hidden from]] us were now revealed, kept from us until that very day.", "kor": "~에게 숨겨둔", "eng": "kept secret from"}, {"page": "44", "word": "admitted into our confidence", "sentence": "She was [[admitted into our confidence]], let in on the secrets we shared with no one else.", "kor": "우리의 신뢰를 얻다/우리의 비밀을 공유하게 되다", "eng": "let in on our secrets"}, {"page": "44", "word": "as often as not", "sentence": "She joined us [[as often as not]], more often than not sitting out on the porch with us.", "kor": "흔히/대개", "eng": "as often as not; usually"}, {"page": "44", "word": "flights of martins", "sentence": "[[Flights of martins]] swept past, whole flocks of the little birds darting overhead.", "kor": "칼새 떼", "eng": "flocks of martins (small birds)"}, {"page": "45", "word": "sweep low over", "sentence": "They would [[sweep low over]] the lawn, skimming along just above the grass.", "kor": "낮게 훑고 지나가다", "eng": "skim low across"}, {"page": "45", "word": "oak chair", "sentence": "She rested in her [[oak chair]], the heavy seat made of solid oak.", "kor": "참나무 의자", "eng": "a chair made of oak"}, {"page": "45", "word": "mimosa", "sentence": "She sat beneath the [[mimosa]], the feathery flowering tree in her yard.", "kor": "미모사 - 나무의 일종", "eng": "a feathery flowering tree"}, {"page": "45", "word": "morbid", "sentence": "Their game had a [[morbid]] streak, a gruesome, ghoulish fascination with death.", "kor": "병적인/으스스한", "eng": "gruesome; unhealthily dark"}, {"page": "45", "word": "carried out", "sentence": "They imagined Boo [[carried out]] feet first — borne dead from the house, in their grim play.", "kor": "들려 나가다 - 죽어서 운구되다", "eng": "carried out of the house (i.e., dead)"}, {"page": "45", "word": "stuffed him up the chimney", "sentence": "In the tale they had [[stuffed him up the chimney]], shoving him up it in their invented story.", "kor": "굴뚝에 밀어 넣다", "eng": "shoved him up the chimney (children's invention)"}, {"page": "45", "word": "notion", "sentence": "It was a silly [[notion]], a wild idea with no truth behind it at all.", "kor": "생각/발상", "eng": "an idea; a fanciful thought"}, {"page": "45", "word": "S-ss-ss", "sentence": "She made a sharp [[S-ss-ss]], a hissing tut of disapproval at the story.", "kor": "혀 차는 소리 - 못마땅함의 표현", "eng": "a hissing click of disapproval"}, {"page": "45", "word": "obsession", "sentence": "The Radleys had become an [[obsession]], a fixation that filled the children's every thought.", "kor": "집착/강박", "eng": "an all-consuming fixation"}, {"page": "45", "word": "confined his passion", "sentence": "Mr. Radley [[confined his passion]] to the Bible, limiting all his fervour to it.", "kor": "열정을 제한하다/가두다", "eng": "limited his passion to"}, {"page": "45", "word": "window boxes", "sentence": "She grew geraniums in [[window boxes]], the little flower troughs along the sills.", "kor": "창문 화분", "eng": "flower boxes on windowsills"}, {"page": "45", "word": "stayed rich", "sentence": "The family [[stayed rich]], remaining wealthy down through the years.", "kor": "부유하게 지내다", "eng": "remained wealthy"}, {"page": "45", "word": "strange way to ask for a lady's hand in marriage", "sentence": "Throwing dirt was a [[strange way to ask for a lady's hand in marriage]], an odd manner of proposing indeed.", "kor": "결혼 신청을 하는 이상한 방식", "eng": "an odd way to propose marriage"}, {"page": "45", "word": "get Miss Maudie's goat", "sentence": "He only said it to [[get Miss Maudie's goat]], to needle and annoy her on purpose.", "kor": "미스 모디를 약 올리다/짜증나게 하다", "eng": "to annoy Miss Maudie on purpose"}, {"page": "45", "word": "defense", "sentence": "She mounted a quick [[defense]], guarding herself against his teasing.", "kor": "방어", "eng": "protecting oneself from attack"}, {"page": "45", "word": "spirited offense", "sentence": "Then she switched to a [[spirited offense]], a lively counter-attack of her own.", "kor": "[ㅅ피리티ㄷ] 활기찬 공격/적극적인 공세", "eng": "a lively counter-attack"}, {"page": "45", "word": "narrowed", "sentence": "Her eyes [[narrowed]], squeezing to thin slits as she sized him up.", "kor": "가늘어지다/눈을 가늘게 뜨다", "eng": "squeezed into a narrow look (of eyes)"}, {"page": "45", "word": "settled her bridgework", "sentence": "She [[settled her bridgework]], clicking the false teeth into place with her tongue.", "kor": "치아 교정물을 제자리에 맞추다", "eng": "clicked her dental bridge into place"}, {"page": "46", "word": "foot-washing Baptist", "sentence": "Mr. Radley was a [[foot-washing Baptist]], a member of a strict old sect that took every rule to the extreme.", "kor": "발 씻기 침례교도 - 극단적으로 엄격한 종파", "eng": "a member of a strict primitive Baptist sect"}, {"page": "46", "word": "shell's", "sentence": "\"My [[shell's]] not as hard as all that,\" she joked — meaning she wasn't really so tough.", "kor": "껍데기/외피", "eng": "my outer shell (i.e., I'm not that hard)"}, {"page": "46", "word": "foot-washing", "sentence": "They practised [[foot-washing]], the solemn ritual of washing one another's feet in church.", "kor": "발 씻기/세족식", "eng": "the ritual washing of feet"}, {"page": "46", "word": "bathtub", "sentence": "She filled the [[bathtub]], the long tub she soaked in each evening.", "kor": "욕조", "eng": "a tub for bathing"}, {"page": "46", "word": "communion", "sentence": "They took [[communion]], the holy sharing of bread and wine.", "kor": "성찬식/영성체", "eng": "the Christian rite of bread and wine"}, {"page": "46", "word": "primitive baptistry", "sentence": "Their [[primitive baptistry]] was old-fashioned, a plain, ancient way of baptising believers.", "kor": "원시적 세례 방식", "eng": "an old-fashioned form of baptism"}, {"page": "46", "word": "closed communion", "sentence": "They kept [[closed communion]], allowing only their own members to take part.", "kor": "폐쇄적 성찬식", "eng": "communion restricted to members only"}, {"page": "46", "word": "pleasure", "sentence": "To them any [[pleasure]], any delight or enjoyment, was a temptation to be resisted.", "kor": "즐거움/쾌락", "eng": "enjoyment; delight"}, {"page": "46", "word": "sin", "sentence": "Flowers, they said, were a [[sin]], an offence in the very eyes of God.", "kor": "죄", "eng": "an offence against God's law"}, {"page": "46", "word": "hell", "sentence": "Such people, they warned, would burn in [[hell]], the place of everlasting fire.", "kor": "지옥", "eng": "the place of eternal punishment"}, {"page": "46", "word": "burn right with me", "sentence": "\"If I'm wrong you'll [[burn right with me]],\" she joked — go to hell alongside me.", "kor": "나와 함께 타버리다", "eng": "burn in hell along with me"}, {"page": "46", "word": "confidence in", "sentence": "She had little [[confidence in]] their preaching, scant trust in a single word of it.", "kor": "신뢰/확신", "eng": "firm trust in"}, {"page": "46", "word": "pulpit Gospel", "sentence": "She doubted the [[pulpit Gospel]], the harsh message thundered from the preacher's stand.", "kor": "[펄핏] 설교단, 교회 설교", "eng": "the preaching heard from the pulpit"}, {"page": "46", "word": "lessened", "sentence": "Scout's faith [[lessened]], growing weaker the more of it she heard.", "kor": "줄어들다/약해지다", "eng": "grew weaker; decreased"}, {"page": "46", "word": "stewing", "sentence": "She pictured the sinners [[stewing]], simmering and suffering slowly in the flames.", "kor": "끓다/시달리다", "eng": "simmering; suffering slowly"}, {"page": "46", "word": "Protestant hells", "sentence": "There were so many [[Protestant hells]], a different fiery doom imagined by each strict sect.", "kor": "개신교의 지옥들", "eng": "the hells imagined by Protestant sects"}, {"page": "46", "word": "acid tongue", "sentence": "Miss Maudie had an [[acid tongue]], a sharp and biting way of speaking.", "kor": "독설가/신랄한 말투", "eng": "a sharp, biting way of speaking"}, {"page": "46", "word": "go about", "sentence": "Folks would [[go about]] saying it, the rumour circulating freely from mouth to mouth.", "kor": "돌아다니다", "eng": "to move about; circulate"}, {"page": "46", "word": "grain of sense", "sentence": "No one with a [[grain of sense]], anyone with the least bit of judgment, would believe it.", "kor": "조금이라도 분별력이 있는 사람", "eng": "anyone with the least bit of sense"}, {"page": "46", "word": "considerable faith", "sentence": "She had [[considerable faith]] in Atticus, a great deal of trust in his word.", "kor": "상당한 믿음", "eng": "a great deal of trust"}, {"page": "46", "word": "told on us", "sentence": "I was afraid she'd [[told on us]], that she had reported all our antics to Atticus.", "kor": "고자질하다", "eng": "reported our misdeeds"}, {"page": "46", "word": "played cat-and-mouse with us", "sentence": "She never [[played cat-and-mouse with us]], never toyed with us cruelly the way some grown-ups did.", "kor": "우리를 가지고 고양이와 쥐 게임을 하다/약 올리다", "eng": "teased us cruelly for sport"}, {"page": "46", "word": "reasonable", "sentence": "She was a [[reasonable]] woman, sensible and fair in everything she said.", "kor": "합리적인/이성적인", "eng": "sensible; fair-minded"}, {"page": "46", "word": "peril of", "sentence": "We were in [[peril of]] hellfire, in real danger of it, the preacher swore.", "kor": "~의 위험에 처한", "eng": "in danger of"}, {"page": "46", "word": "everlasting torment", "sentence": "He promised them [[everlasting torment]], endless, unbroken punishment in the flames.", "kor": "영원한 고통/영벌", "eng": "unending punishment in hell"}, {"page": "46", "word": "incomprehensible", "sentence": "It was [[incomprehensible]] to her, a thing she simply could not understand.", "kor": "이해할 수 없는", "eng": "impossible to understand"}, {"page": "46", "word": "sin by definition", "sentence": "To them, she was a [[sin by definition]], sinful simply by being who she was.", "kor": "정의상 죄인/본질적으로 죄인", "eng": "sinful simply by being what they are"}, {"page": "46", "word": "literally", "sentence": "They took the Bible [[literally]], believing every word exactly as it was written.", "kor": "문자 그대로", "eng": "in the exact words; word for word"}, {"page": "46", "word": "hankerin' after", "sentence": "He was [[hankerin' after]] her flowers, secretly craving and longing for them (dialect).", "kor": "갈망하다/열망하다", "eng": "longing for; craving (dialect)"}, {"page": "46", "word": "loving folks like you love yourself", "sentence": "She believed in God [[loving folks like you love yourself]] — loving people the way you love your own self.", "kor": "하나님이 네 자신을 사랑하듯 사람들을 사랑하신다", "eng": "God loving people as you love yourself"}, {"page": "46", "word": "hardened", "sentence": "Her face [[hardened]], setting firm and unyielding as stone.", "kor": "굳어지다/단호해지다", "eng": "set hard; became unyielding"}, {"page": "47", "word": "hard", "sentence": "Some of those preachers were [[hard]], harsh and rigid in every judgment they made.", "kor": "완고한/엄격한", "eng": "harsh and rigid"}, {"page": "47", "word": "worrying about the next world", "sentence": "Too much [[worrying about the next world]], fretting over the afterlife, made people forget this one.", "kor": "다음 세상을 걱정하다/내세를 걱정하다", "eng": "obsessing over the afterlife"}, {"page": "47", "word": "live in this one", "sentence": "Better to learn to [[live in this one]], to make a good life here on earth.", "kor": "이 세상에서 살다", "eng": "learn to live in this world"}, {"page": "47", "word": "results", "sentence": "She didn't like the [[results]], the sour consequences of all that grim preaching.", "kor": "결과들", "eng": "the consequences; what comes of it"}, {"page": "47", "word": "three-fourths colored folks", "sentence": "The ghost tales were [[three-fourths colored folks]] — three quarters of them drawn from Black folklore.", "kor": "4분의 3은 흑인들의 이야기", "eng": "three-quarters Black folklore (of the stories)"}, {"page": "47", "word": "grimly", "sentence": "She said it [[grimly]], her face stern and unsmiling.", "kor": "엄숙하게/단호하게", "eng": "in a grim, unsmiling way"}, {"page": "47", "word": "move over in the bed and make room for him", "sentence": "\"Did Boo [[move over in the bed and make room for him]]?\" Miss Maudie mocked, teasing the wild rumour.", "kor": "침대에서 자리를 비켜줬어?", "eng": "did you make room for him in the bed? (mockery)"}, {"page": "47", "word": "shut her up", "sentence": "Her sharp question [[shut her up]], silencing the gossip on the spot.", "kor": "입을 다물게 하다", "eng": "silenced her"}, {"page": "47", "word": "crazy", "sentence": "Some thought Mr. Radley was [[crazy]], plain out of his mind.", "kor": "미쳤다고 생각하다", "eng": "insane; out of his mind"}, {"page": "47", "word": "Gracious child", "sentence": "\"[[Gracious child]],\" she exclaimed — a startled 'good heavens!' at what Scout had said.", "kor": "이런/맙소사 - 감탄의 표현", "eng": "Good heavens, child (an exclamation)"}, {"page": "47", "word": "raveling a thread", "sentence": "She kept [[raveling a thread]], pulling one loose from her sleeve as she talked.", "kor": "실을 풀다/이야기의 실마리를 풀다", "eng": "pulling loose a thread (lit. and fig.)"}, {"page": "47", "word": "awakened", "sentence": "I [[awakened]] at dawn, stirring from sleep as the first light came.", "kor": "잠에서 깨다", "eng": "woke from sleep"}, {"page": "47", "word": "emerged from", "sentence": "The boys [[emerged from]] the garage, coming out at last from their hiding place.", "kor": "나오다/벗어나다", "eng": "came out of"}, {"page": "47", "word": "huddle", "sentence": "They broke from their [[huddle]], the tight little whispering knot they had formed.", "kor": "작은 모임/속닥거리는 회의", "eng": "a close, whispering group"}, {"page": "47", "word": "warned", "sentence": "Jem [[warned]] me to keep quiet, giving a stern warning to say nothing.", "kor": "경고하다", "eng": "gave a warning"}, {"page": "47", "word": "high and mighty", "sentence": "He had been [[high and mighty]] all morning, acting grand and superior.", "kor": "잘난 체하는/거만한", "eng": "acting superior; arrogant"}, {"page": "48", "word": "grew ten inches in the night", "sentence": "He acted as if he'd [[grew ten inches in the night]] — suddenly puffed up and superior, as if he'd shot up overnight.", "kor": "밤새 10인치나 큰 것처럼 행동하다 - 갑자기 거만해졌다는 표현", "eng": "acting as if he'd grown overnight (suddenly superior)"}, {"page": "48", "word": "placidly", "sentence": "She answered [[placidly]], calmly and unruffled, without raising her voice.", "kor": "[플래시들리] 차분하게/평온하게", "eng": "calmly; without agitation"}, {"page": "48", "word": "fight down", "sentence": "She tried to [[fight down]] her fear, forcing the rising panic back down inside.", "kor": "억누르다/참다", "eng": "to force down; suppress"}, {"page": "48", "word": "automatic terror", "sentence": "An [[automatic terror]] gripped her, a reflex fear she simply couldn't help.", "kor": "자동적인 공포/본능적인 공포", "eng": "instant, reflex fear"}, {"page": "48", "word": "rising in me", "sentence": "She felt the dread [[rising in me]], swelling up from somewhere deep inside.", "kor": "내 안에서 솟아오르는", "eng": "swelling up inside me"}, {"page": "48", "word": "snug", "sentence": "The tyre felt [[snug]], cosy and close around her like a shell.", "kor": "아늑한/편안한", "eng": "cosy; comfortably sheltered"}, {"page": "48", "word": "fishing pole", "sentence": "Jem fetched a [[fishing pole]], a long thin rod for catching fish.", "kor": "낚싯대", "eng": "a long rod for fishing"}, {"page": "48", "word": "stick it through", "sentence": "He'd [[stick it through]] the shutters, poking the pole right through the slats.", "kor": "밀어 넣다", "eng": "poke it through"}, {"page": "48", "word": "shutters", "sentence": "The [[shutters]] hung crooked, the wooden window-covers loose on their hinges.", "kor": "덧문/셔터", "eng": "hinged window covers"}, {"page": "48", "word": "silver dinner-bell", "sentence": "On the note was a [[silver dinner-bell]], the little bell rung to call folks to supper.", "kor": "은색 저녁 식사 종", "eng": "a small silver bell rung for dinner"}, {"page": "48", "word": "shutterloose", "sentence": "One window was [[shutterloose]], its shutter hanging open and swinging free.", "kor": "덧문이 헐거워진", "eng": "with a loose, hanging shutter"}, {"page": "48", "word": "stick on", "sentence": "The note wouldn't [[stick on]] the pole, refusing to stay fixed to its tip.", "kor": "달라붙다/고정되다", "eng": "to stick in place"}, {"page": "48", "word": "window sill", "sentence": "He aimed for the [[window sill]], the narrow ledge at the bottom of the window.", "kor": "창문턱", "eng": "the ledge at a window's base"}, {"page": "48", "word": "back end of the lot", "sentence": "They crept to the [[back end of the lot]], the far rear of the property.", "kor": "부지의 뒷부분", "eng": "the rear end of the property"}, {"page": "48", "word": "That clear?", "sentence": "\"Don't make a sound — [[That clear?]]\" Jem hissed, meaning 'is that understood?'", "kor": "알겠어?", "eng": "Is that clear? Understood?"}, {"page": "48", "word": "figure", "sentence": "\"I [[figure]] it'll work,\" Jem said — meaning he reckoned or supposed it would.", "kor": "생각하다/추측하다", "eng": "to reckon; suppose"}, {"page": "48", "word": "sit a spell", "sentence": "\"Come [[sit a spell]],\" Miss Maudie called — stay and rest a little while (dialect).", "kor": "잠시 앉아 있다 - 방언", "eng": "sit for a while (dialect)"}, {"page": "48", "word": "shut up", "sentence": "Boo had been [[shut up]] in there for years, kept locked away from the world.", "kor": "갇혀 있다", "eng": "kept locked away"}, {"page": "48", "word": "Uh huh, caughtcha", "sentence": "\"[[Uh huh, caughtcha]]!\" Dill crowed — gotcha, caught you out (dialect).", "kor": "잡았다/들켰어", "eng": "Gotcha! Caught you out! (dialect)"}, {"page": "48", "word": "all the same to you", "sentence": "\"If it's [[all the same to you]],\" he said — if it makes no difference to you either way.", "kor": "네가 상관없다면/어차피 마찬가지라면", "eng": "if it makes no difference to you"}, {"page": "48", "word": "mounted police uniform", "sentence": "Dill claimed his father wore a [[mounted police uniform]], the dress of a policeman who rides on horseback.", "kor": "기마 경찰 제복", "eng": "the uniform of a mounted policeman"}, {"page": "48", "word": "That'n never showed up, did it?", "sentence": "\"[[That'n never showed up, did it?]]\" Jem jeered — that one never came, did it?", "kor": "그건 나타난 적 없지, 그렇지?", "eng": "that one never arrived, did it?"}, {"page": "48", "word": "keep on tellin' 'em", "sentence": "\"Go ahead and [[keep on tellin' 'em]],\" he said — go on telling those lies (dialect).", "kor": "계속 거짓말해봐", "eng": "go on telling them lies (dialect)"}, {"page": "48", "word": "biggest ones", "sentence": "These were his [[biggest ones]], his tallest tales and grandest whoppers.", "kor": "가장 큰 거짓말/허풍", "eng": "his tallest tales; biggest whoppers"}, {"page": "49", "word": "mail plane", "sentence": "His mother had won a [[mail plane]], one of the planes that carried the post.", "kor": "우편 비행기", "eng": "an aircraft carrying the mail"}, {"page": "49", "word": "Nova Scotia", "sentence": "Dill said he had been to [[Nova Scotia]], a far-off province on Canada's east coast.", "kor": "노바 스코샤 - 캐나다의 주", "eng": "a province of eastern Canada"}, {"page": "49", "word": "Brigadier General Joe Wheeler", "sentence": "He claimed kin to [[Brigadier General Joe Wheeler]], a real cavalry general of the Civil War.", "kor": "여단장 조 휠러 - 남북전쟁의 실제 인물", "eng": "a real Confederate cavalry general"}, {"page": "49", "word": "scuttled", "sentence": "He [[scuttled]] across the yard, scurrying along in quick, low little steps.", "kor": "[스커틀ㄷ] 종종걸음으로 움직이다", "eng": "scurried with quick short steps"}, {"page": "49", "word": "knock the front door down", "sentence": "Jem dared him to [[knock the front door down]], to march up and hammer on it.", "kor": "앞문을 두드리다", "eng": "hammer on the front door"}, {"page": "49", "word": "light-pole", "sentence": "She watched from the [[light-pole]], the tall post that carried the electric wires.", "kor": "전신주/가로등 기둥", "eng": "a pole carrying electric lines"}, {"page": "49", "word": "front corner of the lot", "sentence": "Scout stood at the [[front corner of the lot]], the forward corner of the property.", "kor": "부지의 앞 모퉁이", "eng": "the front corner of the property"}, {"page": "49", "word": "edged down", "sentence": "She [[edged down]] the fence, inching along it bit by careful bit.", "kor": "조금씩 움직이다", "eng": "moved down little by little"}, {"page": "49", "word": "curve", "sentence": "Past the [[curve]], the bend where the street turned, lay safety.", "kor": "굽이/모퉁이", "eng": "a bend in the street"}, {"page": "49", "word": "All clear", "sentence": "\"[[All clear]],\" she signalled — no one was about, safe to go.", "kor": "이상 없음/아무도 없음", "eng": "no one around; safe to proceed"}, {"page": "49", "word": "soul in sight", "sentence": "There wasn't a [[soul in sight]], not a single living person to be seen.", "kor": "눈에 보이는 사람 하나 없다", "eng": "not a single person visible"}, {"page": "49", "word": "let the pole out", "sentence": "Jem began to [[let the pole out]], extending it slowly toward the house.", "kor": "장대를 뻗다", "eng": "extend the pole outward"}, {"page": "49", "word": "pushed it toward", "sentence": "He [[pushed it toward]] the window, edging the pole in that direction.", "kor": "밀다", "eng": "pushed it in the direction of"}, {"page": "49", "word": "lacked several inches of", "sentence": "The pole [[lacked several inches of]] reaching, falling just short of the sill.", "kor": "몇 인치가 모자라다", "eng": "was several inches too short to"}, {"page": "49", "word": "leaned over", "sentence": "He [[leaned over]] the fence, bending his body far forward to reach.", "kor": "몸을 앞으로 기울이다", "eng": "bent his body forward"}, {"page": "49", "word": "jabbing motions", "sentence": "He made [[jabbing motions]], poking the pole at the sill in short sharp thrusts.", "kor": "찌르는 동작", "eng": "sharp poking movements"}, {"page": "49", "word": "abandoned my post", "sentence": "I [[abandoned my post]], deserting my lookout spot to come and watch.", "kor": "내 자리를 버리다/경계를 포기하다", "eng": "deserted my lookout position"}, {"page": "49", "word": "get it off the pole", "sentence": "He couldn't [[get it off the pole]], couldn't shake the note free from its tip.", "kor": "장대에서 떼어내다", "eng": "detach it from the pole"}, {"page": "49", "word": "muttered", "sentence": "\"Hurry,\" he [[muttered]], the word breathed out low under his breath.", "kor": "중얼거리다", "eng": "said under his breath"}, {"page": "49", "word": "G'on", "sentence": "\"[[G'on]],\" Dill urged — his clipped country way of saying 'go on.'", "kor": "Go on - 방언", "eng": "go on (dialect)"}, {"page": "49", "word": "gazed around", "sentence": "She [[gazed around]] nervously, looking this way and that for any sign of trouble.", "kor": "두리번거리다", "eng": "looked all around"}, {"page": "49", "word": "flutter to the ground", "sentence": "The note began to [[flutter to the ground]], drifting down loose from the pole.", "kor": "펄럭이며 땅에 떨어지다", "eng": "drift down to the ground"}, {"page": "49", "word": "jab it up", "sentence": "He tried to [[jab it up]], thrusting the pole sharply upward to catch the note.", "kor": "찌르듯 밀어 올리다", "eng": "thrust it sharply upward"}, {"page": "49", "word": "Shoulder up", "sentence": "Suddenly his [[Shoulder up]] — his shoulders hunched up tight with fright.", "kor": "어깨를 움츠리다/어깨가 긴장하다", "eng": "shoulders hunched in tension"}, {"page": "49", "word": "reeled around", "sentence": "He [[reeled around]], spinning unsteadily on his heels.", "kor": "비틀거리며 돌아서다", "eng": "spun around unsteadily"}, {"page": "49", "word": "bloody fangs", "sentence": "She imagined Boo with [[bloody fangs]], dripping teeth straight out of her nightmares.", "kor": "피 묻은 송곳니", "eng": "fangs dripping with blood (imagined)"}, {"page": "49", "word": "all his might", "sentence": "He pulled with [[all his might]], every scrap of strength he had.", "kor": "온 힘을 다해", "eng": "with every bit of his strength"}, {"page": "49", "word": "heart to", "sentence": "She hadn't the [[heart to]] tell him, no stomach or courage for it.", "kor": "~할 용기/마음이 없다", "eng": "lacked the heart to"}, {"page": "49", "word": "told him so", "sentence": "\"I [[told him so]],\" she said smugly — I said this would happen.", "kor": "그럴 줄 알았다고 말하다", "eng": "said I told you so"}, {"page": "49", "word": "trudged along", "sentence": "We [[trudged along]] home, plodding wearily with dragging feet.", "kor": "터덜터덜 걷다", "eng": "plodded along wearily"}, {"page": "49", "word": "dragging", "sentence": "He came [[dragging]] the pole, hauling it limply along the ground behind him.", "kor": "끌다", "eng": "pulling along the ground"}, {"page": "50", "word": "clapper", "sentence": "The bell had lost its [[clapper]], the little swinging tongue that makes it ring.", "kor": "종의 추/종소리를 내는 쇠", "eng": "the swinging tongue inside a bell"}, {"page": "50", "word": "pushed his hat to the back of his head", "sentence": "Atticus [[pushed his hat to the back of his head]], tipping it back to look at them squarely.", "kor": "모자를 뒤로 밀다", "eng": "tipped his hat back on his head"}, {"page": "50", "word": "put his hands on his hips", "sentence": "He [[put his hands on his hips]], planting both fists at his waist.", "kor": "두 손을 허리에 얹다", "eng": "planted his hands on his hips"}, {"page": "50", "word": "filthy", "sentence": "Their clothes were [[filthy]], caked and grimy with dirt.", "kor": "더러운/지저분한", "eng": "dirty; grimy"}, {"page": "50", "word": "enjoy us", "sentence": "He seemed to [[enjoy us]], to find our antics quietly amusing.", "kor": "우리를 즐거워하다/우리와 함께 즐기다", "eng": "finds us amusing; enjoys our company"}, {"page": "50", "word": "dried up", "sentence": "Caught out, Jem [[dried up]], his words drying to nothing in his throat.", "kor": "말이 막히다/말문이 막히다", "eng": "ran out of words; fell silent"}, {"page": "50", "word": "stop tormenting", "sentence": "He told them to [[stop tormenting]] the poor man, to quit persecuting him.", "kor": "괴롭히기를 멈추다", "eng": "stop persecuting"}, {"page": "50", "word": "inquisitive", "sentence": "We were too [[inquisitive]], far too nosy and prying for our own good.", "kor": "[인퀴지티v] 호기심 많은/꼬치꼬치 캐묻는", "eng": "overly curious; prying"}, {"page": "50", "word": "mild term", "sentence": "'Inquisitive' was a [[mild term]] for it, a politely softened word for plain snooping.", "kor": "완화된 표현/부드러운 표현", "eng": "a politely softened word"}, {"page": "50", "word": "likes of us", "sentence": "Boo wanted nothing to do with the [[likes of us]], with people such as we were.", "kor": "우리 같은 사람들", "eng": "people like us"}, {"page": "50", "word": "barged in on", "sentence": "We had [[barged in on]] his privacy, bursting in uninvited on his life.", "kor": "불쑥 들이닥치다", "eng": "burst in on uninvited"}, {"page": "50", "word": "in effect", "sentence": "We were, [[in effect]], spying on him — in practice that's just what it was.", "kor": "사실상/실질적으로", "eng": "in practice; in reality"}, {"page": "50", "word": "seem peculiar", "sentence": "It might [[seem peculiar]] to stay indoors, to appear strange and odd to outsiders.", "kor": "이상해 보이다", "eng": "appear strange or odd"}, {"page": "50", "word": "never occurred to us", "sentence": "It had [[never occurred to us]] that Boo might choose to hide — the thought had never crossed our minds.", "kor": "우리에게 한 번도 떠오르지 않았다", "eng": "never once crossed our minds"}, {"page": "50", "word": "civil", "sentence": "The way to be [[civil]], polite and decent, was simply to leave him be.", "kor": "예의 바른/정중한", "eng": "polite; courteous"}, {"page": "50", "word": "communicate with", "sentence": "If he wanted to [[communicate with]] us, to send us any message, he would.", "kor": "소통하다", "eng": "to exchange messages with"}, {"page": "50", "word": "stay away from", "sentence": "We were to [[stay away from]] that house, to keep well clear of it.", "kor": "멀리하다", "eng": "keep clear of"}, {"page": "50", "word": "asinine", "sentence": "It was an [[asinine]] thing to do, an utterly foolish, stupid stunt.", "kor": "[애서나인] 어리석은/바보 같은", "eng": "utterly foolish (formal)"}, {"page": "50", "word": "putting his life's history on display", "sentence": "We were [[putting his life's history on display]], exhibiting his private life for all to gawk at.", "kor": "그의 삶의 역사를 전시하다", "eng": "exhibiting his private life publicly"}, {"page": "50", "word": "edification", "sentence": "It was for our [[edification]], Atticus said dryly — for our moral instruction (he meant the opposite).", "kor": "[에더피케이션] 교화/계몽", "eng": "moral instruction (mock-formal)"}, {"page": "50", "word": "swell", "sentence": "Jem began to [[swell]], puffing up with hot indignation.", "kor": "부풀다/팽창하다", "eng": "puff up with indignation"}, {"page": "50", "word": "grinned dryly", "sentence": "Atticus [[grinned dryly]], a thin, humourless little smile.", "kor": "건조하게 웃다/씁쓸하게 웃다", "eng": "smiled without warmth or humour"}, {"page": "50", "word": "nonsense", "sentence": "He had had enough of their [[nonsense]], their foolish, pointless games.", "kor": "터무니없는 짓/어리석은 짓", "eng": "foolish behaviour"}, {"page": "50", "word": "gaped", "sentence": "Jem [[gaped]] at him, his mouth hanging open in dismay.", "kor": "[게입ㅌ] 입을 벌리다/아연실색하다", "eng": "stared open-mouthed"}, {"page": "50", "word": "suspiciously firm", "sentence": "Atticus's mouth went [[suspiciously firm]], oddly stiff — as if holding back a smile.", "kor": "의심스럽게 굳은/웃음을 참는 듯 단단한", "eng": "oddly rigid (holding back a smile)"}, {"page": "51", "word": "hold it in line", "sentence": "He fought to [[hold it in line]], to keep his mouth from breaking into a grin.", "kor": "선을 지키다/웃음을 참다", "eng": "to keep it from smiling"}, {"page": "51", "word": "quibbling", "sentence": "Jem tried [[quibbling]], arguing over tiny points to wriggle free.", "kor": "사소한 것에 트집 잡다/논쟁하다", "eng": "arguing over small points"}, {"page": "51", "word": "retrieve", "sentence": "They'd only meant to [[retrieve]] something, to fetch back what was rightfully theirs.", "kor": "되찾다", "eng": "to fetch back"}, {"page": "51", "word": "done in", "sentence": "Jem had been [[done in]], outwitted and trapped by his own father's question.", "kor": "속다/당하다", "eng": "outwitted; defeated by a trick"}, {"page": "51", "word": "oldest lawyer's trick on record", "sentence": "Atticus had used the [[oldest lawyer's trick on record]], the most ancient trap in the lawyer's book.", "kor": "기록상 가장 오래된 변호사의 속임수", "eng": "the most ancient trick in the lawyer's book"}, {"page": "51", "word": "respectful distance", "sentence": "Dill kept a [[respectful distance]], hanging back a politely safe few steps.", "kor": "예의 바른 거리", "eng": "a politely safe distance"}, {"page": "51", "word": "walk toward town", "sentence": "Atticus turned to [[walk toward town]], heading off in the direction of the square.", "kor": "마을 쪽으로 걷다", "eng": "head off in the direction of town"}, {"page": "51", "word": "out of earshot", "sentence": "Once he was [[out of earshot]], too far off to hear a single word.", "kor": "들을 수 없는 거리", "eng": "too far away to hear"}, {"page": "51", "word": "I ain't so sure now!", "sentence": "\"[[I ain't so sure now!]]\" Jem called — meaning he was no longer certain at all (dialect).", "kor": "이제는 그리 확신하지 않아!", "eng": "now I'm not so sure! (dialect)"}], "6": [{"page": "52", "word": "so long", "sentence": "\"[[So long]],\" Dill called as he ran off — a casual, easy way of saying goodbye.", "kor": "잘 있어/안녕 - 작별 인사", "eng": "goodbye (informal farewell)"}, {"page": "52", "word": "leaped over", "sentence": "He [[leaped over]] the ditch, jumping clear across it in a single bound.", "kor": "뛰어넘다", "eng": "jumped across"}, {"page": "52", "word": "driveway", "sentence": "A car sat in the [[driveway]], the paved path that ran up to the house.", "kor": "진입로", "eng": "the path for cars to a house"}, {"page": "52", "word": "whistled bob-white", "sentence": "Jem [[whistled bob-white]], imitating the quail's call as their secret signal.", "kor": "메추리 울음소리로 휘파람을 불다 - 신호", "eng": "whistled a quail call as a signal"}, {"page": "52", "word": "blowing", "sentence": "Not a breath was [[blowing]], the air dead still without the faintest wind.", "kor": "바람 한 점 없다", "eng": "not a breath of wind"}, {"page": "52", "word": "Looka", "sentence": "\"[[Looka]] there!\" Dill cried — his quick country way of saying 'look over there.'", "kor": "Look over there - 방언", "eng": "look over there (dialect)"}, {"page": "52", "word": "constructing", "sentence": "Jem was [[constructing]] a kite, carefully piecing it together stick by stick.", "kor": "만들다/조립하다", "eng": "building; putting together"}, {"page": "52", "word": "stink up", "sentence": "It would [[stink up]] the whole house, filling every room with a foul smell.", "kor": "냄새를 피우다/악취를 풍기다", "eng": "to fill with a bad smell"}, {"page": "52", "word": "lady in the moon", "sentence": "Dill could see the [[lady in the moon]], the figure folk imagine in the moon's bright face.", "kor": "달 속의 여인 - 달을 바라보는 민간 전설", "eng": "the figure folk see in the moon"}, {"page": "52", "word": "dresser", "sentence": "She sat at her [[dresser]], the chest of drawers with a mirror set on top.", "kor": "화장대", "eng": "a mirror-topped chest of drawers"}, {"page": "52", "word": "boarded", "sentence": "He [[boarded]] with relatives that summer, lodging and taking his meals at their house.", "kor": "하숙하다/방을 빌려 살다", "eng": "lodged; rented a room with meals"}, {"page": "52", "word": "change", "sentence": "The