unds of the dark.", "kor": "부드러운 밤의 중얼거림", "eng": "the soft murmuring sounds of night"}, {"page": "53", "word": "peep in", "sentence": "Dill wanted to [[peep in]] the window, to sneak a secret look inside.", "kor": "몰래 들여다보다", "eng": "look in secretly"}, {"page": "53", "word": "loose shutter", "sentence": "There was a [[loose shutter]], one window-cover hanging free of its catch.", "kor": "헐거운 덧문", "eng": "a shutter hanging loose"}, {"page": "53", "word": "get a look at", "sentence": "He hoped to [[get a look at]] Boo, to catch even a single glimpse of him.", "kor": "~을 보다/엿보다", "eng": "manage to see"}, {"page": "53", "word": "keep my fat flopping mouth shut", "sentence": "\"I'd [[keep my fat flopping mouth shut]],\" she promised — keep my big mouth firmly closed.", "kor": "입을 꾹 다물다 - 강한 표현", "eng": "keep my big mouth firmly shut"}, {"page": "53", "word": "sam holy hill", "sentence": "\"What in the [[sam holy hill]] for?\" she demanded — a country way of saying 'the heck.'", "kor": "도대체/대체 - 'hell'의 완곡한 표현", "eng": "'what the heck' (polite for 'hell')"}, {"page": "53", "word": "deep in a book", "sentence": "Atticus was [[deep in a book]], so absorbed in his reading he heard nothing.", "kor": "책에 깊이 빠지다", "eng": "absorbed in a book"}, {"page": "53", "word": "Kingdom coming", "sentence": "He wouldn't notice the [[Kingdom coming]], so lost in his book he'd miss the end of the world.", "kor": "나라가 오는 것도 듣지 못하다 - 아무것도 눈치채지 못하다", "eng": "wouldn't notice the end of the world"}, {"page": "54", "word": "vacation", "sentence": "It was the last night of summer [[vacation]], the school holidays nearly over.", "kor": "방학", "eng": "the school holidays"}, {"page": "54", "word": "dark house in the dark", "sentence": "You can't see into a [[dark house in the dark]], can't peer inside an unlit house at night.", "kor": "어둠 속에서 어두운 집 안을 보다", "eng": "see into a dark house at night"}, {"page": "54", "word": "daytime", "sentence": "He'd never dare in the [[daytime]], in broad daylight whe