": "꽉 끼는/빠져나가기 힘든", "eng": "a very tight fit"}, {"page": "54", "word": "collards", "sentence": "They crawled through the [[collards]], the broad-leaved Southern greens.", "kor": "콜라드 - 남부 잎채소", "eng": "leafy Southern greens"}, {"page": "54", "word": "wake the dead", "sentence": "The rustling could [[wake the dead]], it was loud enough to rouse the buried.", "kor": "죽은 사람도 깨울 것이다 - 매우 시끄럽다는 표현", "eng": "loud enough to wake the dead"}, {"page": "54", "word": "one step per minute", "sentence": "They moved [[one step per minute]], creeping at a single step every sixty seconds.", "kor": "분당 한 걸음", "eng": "one step every minute (extreme caution)"}, {"page": "54", "word": "beckoning", "sentence": "Jem kept [[beckoning]], waving them on with a curling hand.", "kor": "손짓으로 부르다", "eng": "signalling 'come here' with a hand"}, {"page": "54", "word": "squeaked", "sentence": "A board [[squeaked]] underfoot, letting out a thin, high creak.", "kor": "삐걱거리다", "eng": "made a high creaking sound"}, {"page": "54", "word": "Spit on it", "sentence": "\"[[Spit on it]],\" Jem whispered — wet the hinge with spit to stop the squeak.", "kor": "침을 뱉다 - 소리를 없애기 위해", "eng": "wet it with spit (to silence a hinge)"}, {"page": "54", "word": "got us in a box", "sentence": "That gate had [[got us in a box]], trapped us in a tight corner.", "kor": "우리를 궁지에 몰아넣다/함정에 빠뜨리다", "eng": "trapped us; cornered us"}, {"page": "54", "word": "spat ourselves dry", "sentence": "We [[spat ourselves dry]], spitting on the hinge until our mouths had no spit left.", "kor": "침이 마를 때까지 뱉다", "eng": "spat until our mouths were dry"}, {"page": "54", "word": "lifting it aside", "sentence": "He opened it by [[lifting it aside]], raising the gate to one side rather than swinging it.", "kor": "옆으로 들어 올리다", "eng": "raising it to one side"}, {"page": "54", "word": "resting it on", "sentence": "He carried it, [[resting it on]] the fence, leaning it carefully against the rails.", "kor": "~에 기대다", "eng": "leaning it against"}, {"page