": "66", "word": "new wore off", "sentence": "Soon the [[new wore off]], the first thrill of it fading away.", "kor": "새것의 느낌이 사라지다", "eng": "the novelty faded"}, {"page": "66", "word": "burdensome task", "sentence": "He set himself the [[burdensome task]], a weighty, wearying duty, of fixing the watch.", "kor": "부담스러운 임무", "eng": "a heavy, wearying duty (mock-formal)"}, {"page": "66", "word": "ascertaining", "sentence": "He set about [[ascertaining]] what was wrong, finding out for certain what ailed it.", "kor": "[애썰테이닝] 확인하다/알아내다", "eng": "finding out for certain (formal)"}, {"page": "66", "word": "fair job", "sentence": "He had done a [[fair job]], a passable piece of work, he reckoned.", "kor": "꽤 잘 해내다", "eng": "a passable piece of work (self-graded)"}, {"page": "66", "word": "spring", "sentence": "He pried out the [[spring]], the coiled metal that drives the watch.", "kor": "용수철/스프링", "eng": "the coiled metal that powers a watch"}, {"page": "66", "word": "tiny pieces", "sentence": "It lay in [[tiny pieces]], dozens of very small parts spread out.", "kor": "아주 작은 조각들", "eng": "very small parts"}, {"page": "66", "word": "would not run", "sentence": "Afterward it [[would not run]] at all, dead as a doornail.", "kor": "작동하지 않다", "eng": "refused to work (deadpan punchline)"}, {"page": "66", "word": "holding his ears", "sentence": "Atticus mimed [[holding his ears]], covering them in mock despair.", "kor": "귀를 잡다", "eng": "covering his ears (in mock despair)"}, {"page": "66", "word": "shaking his head from side to side", "sentence": "He kept [[shaking his head from side to side]], wagging it in disbelief.", "kor": "고개를 좌우로 흔들다", "eng": "shaking his head in disbelief"}, {"page": "66", "word": "gotta good mind to", "sentence": "\"I [[gotta good mind to]] write him a letter,\" Jem said — half a mind to (dialect).", "kor": "마음이 굳게 먹어지다/하고 싶다", "eng": "have half a mind to (dialect)"}, {"page": "66", "word": "on the verge of", "sentence": "She was [[on the verge of]] ask