ur knot-hole with cement"}, {"page": "67", "word": "muttered", "sentence": "\"Don't cry,\" Jem [[muttered]], the words low and anxious.", "kor": "중얼거리다", "eng": "said in a low, anxious voice"}, {"page": "67", "word": "dinner", "sentence": "They came home for [[dinner]], the midday meal as Southerners called it.", "kor": "점심 - 남부 방언으로 점심을 dinner라고 함", "eng": "the midday meal (Southern usage)"}, {"page": "67", "word": "bolted his food", "sentence": "Jem [[bolted his food]], gulping it down in a great hurry.", "kor": "음식을 급히 먹다/허겁지겁 먹다", "eng": "gulped his food down fast"}, {"page": "67", "word": "Hasn't passed by yet", "sentence": "\"[[Hasn't passed by yet]],\" Jem reported — Mr. Radley hadn't yet walked past (dialect).", "kor": "아직 지나가지 않았다", "eng": "he hasn't walked past yet (dialect)"}, {"page": "67", "word": "repeated his vigil", "sentence": "He [[repeated his vigil]], keeping up his patient, watchful waiting once more.", "kor": "[vl쥐얼] 불침번, 철야, 목적을 가지고 잠들지 않고 경계하거나 감시하는 행위, 감시를 반복하다/망을 보다", "eng": "kept up his watchful waiting again"}, {"page": "68", "word": "yonder", "sentence": "\"He's coming [[yonder]],\" Jem said — over there, in the distance (dialect).", "kor": "저기/저쪽 - 방언", "eng": "over there (dialect)"}, {"page": "68", "word": "ought to know", "sentence": "Mr. Radley [[ought to know]] about the dying tree, he surely must know.", "kor": "알아야 한다", "eng": "should know; must surely know"}, {"page": "68", "word": "meditative pat", "sentence": "He gave the post a [[meditative pat]], a slow, thoughtful little tap.", "kor": "생각에 잠겨 가볍게 두드리다", "eng": "a slow, thoughtful pat"}, {"page": "68", "word": "deep in thought", "sentence": "Jem stood [[deep in thought]], lost far away in his own mind.", "kor": "생각에 깊이 잠기다", "eng": "lost in thought"}, {"page": "68", "word": "working himself into a bad humor", "sentence": "He was [[working himself into a bad humor]], talking himself into a black mood.", "kor": "나쁜 기분으로 빠져들다/화를 돋우다", "eng": "talking himself into a bad temper"},