ought one another"}, {"page": "69", "word": "seasons would change", "sentence": "Folks said the [[seasons would change]], that summer and winter would turn at last.", "kor": "계절이 바뀔 것이다", "eng": "the seasons would turn"}, {"page": "69", "word": "burdened with", "sentence": "He felt [[burdened with]] guilt, weighed down by it day and night.", "kor": "짐을 지다/~으로 부담을 느끼다", "eng": "weighed down by"}, {"page": "69", "word": "contributing to", "sentence": "Their carelessness was [[contributing to]] the trouble, helping to cause it.", "kor": "~에 기여하다", "eng": "adding to; helping cause"}, {"page": "69", "word": "aberrations of nature", "sentence": "The freak snow was one of those [[aberrations of nature]], a strange break from nature's normal course.", "kor": "[애버레이션ㅅ] 자연의 이상 현상들", "eng": "freak departures from nature's normal course"}, {"page": "69", "word": "causing unhappiness", "sentence": "The cold spell was [[causing unhappiness]], bringing misery to the whole town.", "kor": "불행을 야기하다", "eng": "bringing unhappiness"}, {"page": "69", "word": "discomfort", "sentence": "It brought real [[discomfort]], a physical unease no one could shake.", "kor": "불편함", "eng": "physical unease"}, {"page": "69", "word": "caused hardly a ripple", "sentence": "Her death [[caused hardly a ripple]], barely disturbing anyone in town.", "kor": "거의 파문을 일으키지 않다", "eng": "barely disturbed anyone"}, {"page": "69", "word": "seldom saw her", "sentence": "We [[seldom saw her]], hardly ever catching a glimpse of her.", "kor": "거의 그녀를 보지 못하다", "eng": "rarely saw her"}, {"page": "69", "word": "watered her cannas", "sentence": "Once in a while she [[watered her cannas]], tending the tall canna flowers in her bed.", "kor": "칸나 꽃에 물을 주다", "eng": "watered her canna flowers"}, {"page": "69", "word": "got her at last", "sentence": "Old age [[got her at last]], finally carrying her off.", "kor": "마침내 그녀를 잡았다/죽였다", "eng": "finally carried her off (killed her)"}, {"page": "69", "word": "natural causes", "sentence": "She died of [[natural causes]], of age and illness, not by any harm.", "kor": "자연사/자연적인 원인으로", "eng": "death from age or illness, not violence"}, {"page": "69", "word": "disappointment", "sentence": "To our [[disappointment]], much to our letdown, nothing exciting happened.", "kor": "실망스럽게도", "eng": "to our disappointment"}, {"page": "69", "word": "sternly", "sentence": "Atticus spoke [[sternly]], in a strict and firm tone.", "kor": "엄하게/단호하게", "eng": "in a strict, firm way"}, {"page": "69", "word": "restrained", "sentence": "Calpurnia [[restrained]] her, holding her back by the arm.", "kor": "억제하다/말리다", "eng": "held back; stopped"}, {"page": "69", "word": "touchous", "sentence": "Mr. Avery was [[touchous]] about it, touchy and quick to take offence (dialect).", "kor": "예민한/민감한 - 방언", "eng": "touchy; easily offended (dialect)"}, {"page": "69", "word": "wouldn't do", "sentence": "It [[wouldn't do]] to laugh, it would not be wise at all.", "kor": "소용없다/좋지 않다", "eng": "would not be wise"}, {"page": "69", "word": "push him any", "sentence": "\"Don't [[push him any]] further,\" she said — don't press him a bit more.", "kor": "더 이상 몰아붙이다", "eng": "press him any further"}, {"page": "69", "word": "notion", "sentence": "She had a [[notion]] about it, a faint, half-formed idea.", "kor": "생각/느낌", "eng": "a vague idea or feeling"}, {"page": "69", "word": "not solely confined to", "sentence": "The cold was [[not solely confined to]] their street, not limited only to it.", "kor": "단지 ~에만 국한되지 않다", "eng": "not limited only to"}, {"page": "69", "word": "no firm basis", "sentence": "Her fear had [[no firm basis]], no solid grounds at all.", "kor": "확실한 근거가 없다", "eng": "no solid grounds"}, {"page": "69", "word": "twitch", "sentence": "It was just a [[twitch]] of feeling, an instinctive gut sense of unease.", "kor": "경련/직감 - 여기서는 막연한 느낌", "eng": "a gut feeling; an instinctive twinge"}, {"page": "69", "word": "nearly died of fright", "sentence": "She [[nearly died of fright]], almost frightened clean to death.", "kor": "[f롸이ㅌ] 공포로 거의 죽을 뻔하다", "eng": "was almost frightened to death"}, {"page": "69", "word": "keep up", "sentence": "If the snow could only [[keep up]], if it just continued, they might build something.", "kor": "계속되다", "eng": "to continue"}, {"page": "69", "word": "watery", "sentence": "The snow was thin and [[watery]], more like wet slush than real snow.", "kor": "물기가 많은/묽은", "eng": "thin and wet; like water"}, {"page": "70", "word": "quote", "sentence": "He could [[quote]] the verse exactly, repeating its words one for one.", "kor": "인용하다", "eng": "to repeat someone's exact words"}, {"page": "70", "word": "entrusted with", "sentence": "Mr. Avery was [[entrusted with]] the siren, given the charge of sounding it.", "kor": "~을 맡다/위임받다", "eng": "given the responsibility of"}, {"page": "70", "word": "issuing public announcements", "sentence": "He was in charge of [[issuing public announcements]], making news known to the whole town.", "kor": "공공 공지를 발표하다", "eng": "making announcements to the town"}, {"page": "70", "word": "wedding invitations", "sentence": "He even handled the [[wedding invitations]], the cards inviting folks to weddings.", "kor": "결혼 초대장", "eng": "invitations to weddings"}, {"page": "70", "word": "setting off the fire siren", "sentence": "He was responsible for [[setting off the fire siren]], sounding the alarm when fire broke out.", "kor": "화재 경보를 울리다", "eng": "sounding the fire alarm"}, {"page": "70", "word": "giving first-aid instructions", "sentence": "He took charge of [[giving first-aid instructions]], directing emergency care.", "kor": "응급처치 지시를 내리다", "eng": "giving emergency medical directions"}, {"page": "70", "word": "called us to order", "sentence": "Atticus [[called us to order]], commanding our attention at once.", "kor": "우리를 진정시키다/주의를 집중시키다", "eng": "commanded our attention"}, {"page": "70", "word": "haven't the slightest idea", "sentence": "\"I [[haven't the slightest idea]],\" she admitted — no idea