ect)"}, {"page": "71", "word": "carry off", "sentence": "The frost would [[carry off]] her flowers, killing them all.", "kor": "쓸어가다/죽이다", "eng": "kill off; sweep away"}, {"page": "71", "word": "azaleas", "sentence": "Her [[azaleas]] would die, the flowering shrubs frozen black.", "kor": "[어zㅔ일리어ㅅ] 철쭉/진달래", "eng": "flowering shrubs"}, {"page": "71", "word": "sunhat", "sentence": "She wore a wide [[sunhat]], the broad-brimmed hat to keep off the sun.", "kor": "햇빛 가리개 모자", "eng": "a wide-brimmed hat against the sun"}, {"page": "71", "word": "glistened", "sentence": "The wet leaves [[glistened]], shining with melted snow.", "kor": "반짝이다", "eng": "sparkled; shone wetly"}, {"page": "71", "word": "burlap bags", "sentence": "She covered the plants with [[burlap bags]], sacks of coarse, rough cloth.", "kor": "삼베 자루", "eng": "sacks of coarse woven cloth"}, {"page": "71", "word": "Heavens alive", "sentence": "\"[[Heavens alive]]!\" she cried — a startled 'good heavens!'", "kor": "세상에/맙소사", "eng": "good heavens! (exclamation)"}, {"page": "71", "word": "peach basket", "sentence": "Jem carried a [[peach basket]], the kind used to gather peaches.", "kor": "복숭아 바구니", "eng": "a basket used for peaches"}, {"page": "71", "word": "haul it off", "sentence": "They would [[haul it off]], carrying the snow away by the basketful.", "kor": "운반하다/가져가다", "eng": "carry it away"}, {"page": "71", "word": "narrowed", "sentence": "Her eyes [[narrowed]], squeezing thin with suspicion.", "kor": "가늘어지다", "eng": "narrowed (of eyes, in suspicion)"}, {"page": "71", "word": "slushy operation", "sentence": "It was a [[slushy operation]], a wet, sloppy job.", "kor": "질척한 작업", "eng": "a wet, slushy job"}, {"page": "71", "word": "rake up", "sentence": "They tried to [[rake up]] the snow, gathering it with a rake.", "kor": "갈퀴로 모으다", "eng": "gather with a rake"}, {"page": "71", "word": "Walk back in your tracks", "sentence": "\"[[Walk back in your tracks]],\" Jem said — return stepping in your own footprints.