ng with amusement (of eyes)"}, {"page": "72", "word": "sort of shaped like", "sentence": "It was [[sort of shaped like]] Mr. Avery, roughly resembling him.", "kor": "어느 정도 ~처럼 생긴", "eng": "roughly resembling"}, {"page": "72", "word": "saving the public parts", "sentence": "He molded it carefully, [[saving the public parts]], covering what decency required.", "kor": "공개적인 부분들을 남겨두다", "eng": "covering the parts decency requires"}, {"page": "72", "word": "bits of wood", "sentence": "He stuck on [[bits of wood]], little chips for buttons.", "kor": "나무 조각들", "eng": "small pieces of wood"}, {"page": "72", "word": "cross", "sentence": "Mr. Avery got [[cross]], annoyed and short-tempered about the likeness.", "kor": "짜증난/화난", "eng": "annoyed; bad-tempered"}, {"page": "72", "word": "stick of stovewood", "sentence": "He added a [[stick of stovewood]], one length of firewood.", "kor": "난로용 장작 한 개", "eng": "one piece of firewood"}, {"page": "72", "word": "completed the picture", "sentence": "That [[completed the picture]], finishing the likeness perfectly.", "kor": "그림을 완성하다", "eng": "finished the likeness"}, {"page": "72", "word": "shyly", "sentence": "Jem grinned [[shyly]], pleased but bashful.", "kor": "수줍게", "eng": "in a shy, modest way"}, {"page": "72", "word": "dinner", "sentence": "They went in for [[dinner]], the noon meal as Southerners called it.", "kor": "점심", "eng": "the midday meal (Southern usage)"}, {"page": "72", "word": "jim-dandy job", "sentence": "\"A [[jim-dandy job]],\" Atticus said — a fine, excellent piece of work (dialect).", "kor": "훌륭한 일 - 방언", "eng": "an excellent piece of work (dialect)"}, {"page": "72", "word": "become of you", "sentence": "\"What will [[become of you]], child?\" — what will ever happen to you?", "kor": "너에게 어떤 일이 생길지", "eng": "what will happen to you"}, {"page": "72", "word": "ears reddened", "sentence": "His [[ears reddened]] with pleasure, going pink at the praise.", "kor": "귀가 빨개지다", "eng": "his ears went red (with pleasure)"}, 