ld [[cease to be]] Mr. Avery, stop being him entirely.", "kor": "더 이상 ~이 아니게 되다", "eng": "to stop being"}, {"page": "73", "word": "making caricatures", "sentence": "\"You're [[making caricatures]],\" Atticus chuckled — drawing mocking, exaggerated likenesses.", "kor": "풍자 만화를 만들다", "eng": "drawing mocking exaggerated portraits"}, {"page": "73", "word": "triumphant", "sentence": "Jem looked [[triumphant]], glowing with victory.", "kor": "의기양양한/승리에 찬", "eng": "glowing with victory"}, {"page": "73", "word": "jammed", "sentence": "He [[jammed]] a hat on it, shoving it down hard.", "kor": "밀어 넣다/쑤셔 넣다", "eng": "shoved; stuffed"}, {"page": "73", "word": "hedge-clippers", "sentence": "He stuck Miss Maudie's [[hedge-clippers]] in its hand, the shears for trimming hedges.", "kor": "울타리 가위", "eng": "shears for trimming hedges"}, {"page": "73", "word": "crook of his arm", "sentence": "He carried them in the [[crook of his arm]], cradled in the bend of his elbow.", "kor": "팔의 굽은 부분", "eng": "the bend of his elbow"}, {"page": "73", "word": "fussing", "sentence": "Miss Maudie came [[fussing]], making a great show of complaint.", "kor": "법석을 떨다/투덜거리다", "eng": "making a show of complaint"}, {"page": "73", "word": "accomplishments", "sentence": "She admired Jem's [[accomplishments]], the clever things he had achieved.", "kor": "업적들/성취들", "eng": "things achieved; feats"}, {"page": "73", "word": "strolled over", "sentence": "Atticus [[strolled over]], walking across at an easy, unhurried pace.", "kor": "천천히 걸어가다", "eng": "walked over unhurriedly"}, {"page": "73", "word": "engaged in", "sentence": "They were [[engaged in]] talk, caught up in conversation.", "kor": "참여하다", "eng": "taking part in"}, {"page": "73", "word": "arm-waving conversation", "sentence": "It was an [[arm-waving conversation]], full of waving hands and gestures.", "kor": "팔을 흔들며 나누는 대화", "eng": "a conversation full of waving arms"}, {"page": "73", "word": "erected", "sentence": "Jem had [[erected]] a fine snowman, b