 creases.", "kor": "작은 선들의 그물망", "eng": "a web of fine lines"}, {"page": "79", "word": "crisscrossed", "sentence": "Cuts [[crisscrossed]] her skin, crossing this way and that.", "kor": "교차하다", "eng": "crossed over each other"}, {"page": "79", "word": "brown with dirt and dried blood", "sentence": "Her hands were [[brown with dirt and dried blood]], stained with soil and old blood.", "kor": "흙과 말라붙은 피로 갈색인", "eng": "stained with soil and dried blood"}, {"page": "79", "word": "get a colored man", "sentence": "She'd [[get a colored man]] to help, hire a Black workman (in the phrasing of the day).", "kor": "흑인 일꾼을 고용하다", "eng": "hire a Black workman (dated phrasing)"}, {"page": "79", "word": "no note of sacrifice", "sentence": "She said it with [[no note of sacrifice]], no hint of feeling sorry for herself.", "kor": "희생의 기색이 없는", "eng": "with no hint of self-sacrifice"}, {"page": "80", "word": "rake him up", "sentence": "\"I'll [[rake him up]] in spring,\" she said of the snowman's remains — scrape him into a pile.", "kor": "갈퀴로 끌어모으다", "eng": "scrape him into a pile with a rake"}, {"page": "80", "word": "jiffy", "sentence": "She'd have it cleared in a [[jiffy]], in no time at all (dialect).", "kor": "순식간에/금방 - 방언", "eng": "in no time at all (dialect)"}, {"page": "80", "word": "lips moving silently", "sentence": "Scout stood with [[lips moving silently]], her mouth working without a sound.", "kor": "입술이 소리 없이 움직이다", "eng": "lips working without sound"}, {"page": "80", "word": "put her hands to her head", "sentence": "She [[put her hands to her head]], clapping them to it in dismay.", "kor": "머리에 손을 얹다", "eng": "clapped her hands to her head"}, {"page": "80", "word": "whooped", "sentence": "Miss Maudie [[whooped]], bursting into a great whooping laugh.", "kor": "환호하다/크게 웃다", "eng": "burst into a whooping laugh"}, {"page": "80", "word": "chuckling", "sentence": "She walked off [[chuckling]], laughing softly to herself.", "kor": "킬킬거리다/낮게 웃다", "eng": "laughing quietly to herself"}], "9": [{"page": "81", "word": "take that back", "sentence": "\"[[Take that back]]!\" she demanded — withdraw the insult you just said.", "kor": "취소하다/철회하다", "eng": "withdraw what you said"}, {"page": "81", "word": "thin time", "sentence": "They were having a [[thin time]] of it, a hard, lean stretch with little to spare.", "kor": "힘든 시기/어려운 때", "eng": "a hard, difficult period"}, {"page": "81", "word": "clenched", "sentence": "Her fists were [[clenched]], squeezed white-knuckled tight.", "kor": "꽉 쥔/주먹을 쥔", "eng": "squeezed tight (of fists)"}, {"page": "81", "word": "let fly", "sentence": "She nearly [[let fly]] at him, ready to throw a punch.", "kor": "주먹을 날리다/공격하다", "eng": "to throw a punch"}, {"page": "81", "word": "wear me out", "sentence": "Atticus would [[wear me out]] if I fought, give me a whipping (dialect).", "kor": "혼내주다/지치게 하다", "eng": "to give me a beating (dialect)"}, {"page": "81", "word": "hold in", "sentence": "She had to [[hold in]] her temper, keeping it bottled up.", "kor": "참다/억누르다", "eng": "to keep one's temper in check"}, {"page": "81", "word": "common", "sentence": "He had called Atticus [[common]], a low, vulgar insult.", "kor": "천박한/상스러운", "eng": "vulgar; low-class (an insult)"}, {"page": "81", "word": "mildly", "sentence": "Atticus answered [[mildly]], gently and without any heat.", "kor": "온화하게/부드럽게", "eng": "gently; without heat"}, {"page": "81", "word": "amusement", "sentence": "There was [[amusement]] in his eyes, a quiet, private enjoyment.", "kor": "즐거움/재미있어함", "eng": "quiet enjoyment; entertainment"}, {"page": "81", "word": "compromise", "sentence": "They reached a [[compromise]], a deal where each side gave up a little.", "kor": "타협/절충", "eng": "a deal where both sides yield a little"}, {"page": "81", "word": "campaign", "sentence": "Aunt Alexandra began a [[campaign]], a long, organized effort to change her.", "kor": "캠페인/계획적인 노력", "eng": "an organized, sustained effort"}, {"page": "81", "word": "dose", "sentence": "She'd had a [[dose]] of it already, one trying round of the aunt's lectures.", "kor": "한 번 경험/한 차례", "eng": "one round; one experience of"}, {"page": "81", "word": "sinking spells", "sentence": "Aunt Rachel had [[sinking spells]], sudden faint, weak turns (the dialect of a hypochondriac).", "kor": "가라앉는 느낌/기운이 없는 발작", "eng": "fainting fits (dialect hypochondria)"}, {"page": "81", "word": "gastric complaints", "sentence": "She suffered [[gastric complaints]], assorted stomach troubles.", "kor": "위장 불편/소화 문제", "eng": "stomach troubles"}, {"page": "81", "word": "afflicted with", "sentence": "He was [[afflicted with]] gout, suffering badly from it.", "kor": "고통받다/시달리다", "eng": "suffering from"}, {"page": "81", "word": "ringworm", "sentence": "The boy had [[ringworm]], the itchy ring-shaped fungal rash on his skin.", "kor": "백선/피부 곰팡이 감염", "eng": "a fungal skin infection"}, {"page": "81", "word": "worrying another bone", "sentence": "Atticus was [[worrying another bone]] now, gnawing at a different problem, like a dog with a new bone.", "kor": "다른 문제를 걱정하다/다른 뼈를 물고 늘어지다", "eng": "gnawing at a different problem (dog image)"}, {"page": "81", "word": "runnin' a still", "sentence": "A neighbour was [[runnin' a still]], secretly brewing illegal whiskey (dialect).", "kor": "밀주를 만들다/불법으로 술을 제조하다", "eng": "running an illegal whiskey still"}, {"page": "81", "word": "settlement", "sentence": "It happened in a small [[settlement]], a little backwoods community.", "kor": "정착촌/마을", "eng": "a small community; hamlet"}, {"page": "81", "word": "clean-living", "sentence": "They were [[clean-living]] folk, leading decent, upright lives.", "kor": "단정하게 사는/올바르게 사는", "eng": "living a decent, upright life"}, {"page": "81", "word": "high talk", "sentence": "There had been [[high talk]] about it, serious, weighty gossip.", "kor": "심각한 이야기/중요한 소문", "eng": "serious, weighty talk"}, {"page": "81", "word": "to the effect that", "sentence": "Word came [[to the effect that]] Atticus would defend a Black man, meaning roughly that.", "kor": "~라는 취지로/~라는 내용으로", "eng": "meaning roughly that"}, {"page": "81", "word": "peculiar", "sentence": "It was a [[peculiar]] case, an odd and unusual one.", "kor": "특이한/이상한", "eng": "odd; unusual"}, {"page": "82", "word": "session", "sentence": "It would come up at the next [[session]], the court's coming term of business.", "kor": "개정 기간/법원 개회 기간", "eng": "the court's term of business"}, {"page": "82", "word": "postponement", "sentence": "There had been a [[postponement]], the trial put off to a later date.", "kor": "연기/미룸", "eng": "a delay to a later date"}, {"page": "82", "word": "hold up my head in town", "sentence": "If I refused, I couldn't [[hold up my head in town]], couldn't keep my self-respect among my neighbours.", "kor": "마을에서 고개를 들고 다니다/자존심을 지키다", "eng": "keep my self-respect in town"}, {"page": "82", "word": "legislature", "sentence": "I couldn't sit in the [[legislature]], the state's law-making body, if I backed down.", "kor": "의회/입법부", "eng": "the state's law-making body"}, {"page": "82", "word": "by the nature of", "sentence": "[[By the nature of]] the work, by its very character, lawyers must take hard cases.", "kor": "~의 본질상/~의 특성에 따라", "eng": "because of the very nature of"}, {"page": "82", "word": "hold your head high", "sentence": "\"[[Hold your head high]],\" he told her — keep your dignity and don't be ashamed.", "kor": "고개를 높이 들다/당당하게 있다", "eng": "keep your dignity; don't be ashamed"}, {"page": "82", "word": "let 'em get your goat", "sentence": "\"Don't [[let 'em get your goat]],\" he said — don't let them provoke you into a fight.", "kor": "약을 올리게 하다/화나게 하다", "eng": "let them provoke you (idiom)"}, {"page": "82", "word": "fighting with your head", "sentence": "\"Try [[fighting with your head]] for a change,\" he said — using your wits instead of your fists.", "kor": "머리로 싸우다/이성으로 대처하다", "eng": "fighting with intelligence, not fists"}, {"page": "82", "word": "resist learning", "sentence": "She seemed to [[resist learning]], stubbornly refusing to be taught (he teased).", "kor": "배움을 거부하다/배우기를 싫어하다", "eng": "refuses to be taught (gentle joke)"}, {"page": "82", "word": "licked", "sentence": "We had been [[licked]] before we started, beaten from the very beginning (dialect).", "kor": "지다/패배하다", "eng": "beaten; defeated (dialect)"}, {"page": "82", "word": "sole surviving", "sentence": "He was the [[sole surviving]] veteran, the only one of his company still living.", "kor": "유일하게 살아남은", "eng": "the only one still living"}, {"page": "82", "word": "Confederate veteran", "sentence": "He was a [[Confederate veteran]], an old soldier of the South's army.", "kor": "남부 연합 참전 용사", "eng": "a soldier of the Confederate army"}, {"page": "82", "word": "inordinately vain", "sentence": "He was [[inordinately vain]], absurdly proud of himself.", "kor": "지나치게 허영심이 강한", "eng": "excessively proud of himself"}, {"page": "82", "word": "called on", "sentence": "He [[called on]] the neighbours, paying them regular visits.", "kor": "방문하다", "eng": "paid visits to"}, {"page": "82", "word": "respectfully", "sentence": "We listened [[respectfully]], with proper politeness.", "kor": "존경스럽게/공손하게", "eng": "with respect and politeness"}, {"page": "82", "word": "rehash", "sentence": "He liked to [[rehash]] old battles, going over the same ground again and again.", "kor": "되풀이하다/다시 논하다", "eng": "to go over the same old ground"}, {"page": "82", "word": "Missouri Compromise", "sentence": "He'd lecture on the [[Missouri Compromise]], the famous 1820 deal over slave and free states.", "kor": "미주리 타협 - 1820년의 역사적 협정", "eng": "the 1820 slave-state/free-state deal"}, {"page": "82", "word": "furthermore", "sentence": "\"[[Furthermore]],\" he added gravely — his formal word for 'moreover.'", "kor": "더욱이/게다가", "eng": "in addition; moreover (formal)"}, {"page": "82", "word": "whip", "sentence": "The South could still [[whip]] the North, he insisted — beat them in a fight (dialect).", "kor": "이기다/물리치다", "eng": "to defeat (dialect)"}, {"page": "82", "word": "Stonewall Jackson", "sentence": "He worshipped [[Stonewall Jackson]], the famous Confederate general.", "kor": "스톤월 잭슨 - 남부 연합의 유명한 장군", "eng": "the famed Confederate general"}, {"page": "82", "word": "beg your pardon", "sentence": "\"[[Beg your pardon]], sir,\" he'd say — a reverent little correction.", "kor": "실례합니다/죄송합니다", "eng": "excuse me (here: reverent correction)"}, {"page": "82", "word": "Ol' Blue Light", "sentence": "He called him [[Ol' Blue Light]], Stonewall Jackson's old nickname.", "kor": "올드 블루 라이트 - 스톤월 잭슨의 별명", "eng": "Stonewall Jackson's nickname"}, {"page": "82", "word": "saintly brow", "sentence": "He spoke of the general's [[saintly brow]], his holy, noble forehead (with mock reverence).", "kor": "성스러운 이마/거룩한 영혼", "eng": "a holy, saintly forehead (mock-pious)"}, {"page": "83", "word": "crawled into", "sentence": "Scout [[crawled into]] his lap, climbing up to sit on it.", "kor": "기어들어가다", "eng": "climbed into (a lap)"}, {"page": "83", "word": "tucked my head", "sentence": "She [[tucked my head]] under his chin, burying it against him.", "kor": "머리를 파묻다", "eng": "buried my head"}, {"page": "83", "word": "rocked me gently", "sentence": "He [[rocked me gently]], swaying her softly back and forth.", "kor": "부드럽게 흔들다", "eng": "swayed me softly"}, {"page": "83", "word": "disgrace", "sentence": "Fighting was a [[disgrace]], a shame to the family.", "kor": "수치/망신", "eng": "shame; dishonour"}, {"page": "83", "word": "drew a bead on", "sentence": "Cecil [[drew a bead on]] her, taking careful aim with his taunts.", "kor": "조준하다/겨냥하다", "eng": "took careful aim at"}, {"page": "83", "word": "cow—ward", "sentence": "\"[[Cow—ward]]!\" he jeered, drawing the insult out long and loud.", "kor": "겁쟁이 - coward의 강조 발음", "eng": "coward, drawn out for insult"}, {"page": "83", "word": "let Atticus down", "sentence": "She didn't want to [[let Atticus down]], to disappoint her father.", "kor": "애티커스를 실망시키다", "eng": "to disappoint