 "word": "sighing", "sentence": "She lay [[sighing]], letting out long, weary breaths.", "kor": "한숨 쉬기", "eng": "letting out sighs"}, {"page": "83", "word": "induce", "sentence": "Nothing could [[induce]] her to like it, nothing could coax or persuade her.", "kor": "유도하다/설득하다", "eng": "to persuade; coax"}, {"page": "83", "word": "compensation", "sentence": "Snow was the one [[compensation]], the single thing that made up for the rest.", "kor": "보상/위안", "eng": "something making up for a loss"}, {"page": "83", "word": "religious holiday", "sentence": "Christmas was a [[religious holiday]], a holy festival as well as a feast.", "kor": "종교적 명절", "eng": "a religious festival day"}, {"page": "84", "word": "on principle", "sentence": "Uncle Jack disliked children [[on principle]], as a fixed general rule.", "kor": "원칙적으로/원칙상", "eng": "as a matter of principle"}, {"page": "84", "word": "disapproved of", "sentence": "He [[disapproved of]] their games, frowning upon them.", "kor": "못마땅해하다/반대하다", "eng": "frowned upon; objected to"}, {"page": "84", "word": "ingenuous diversions", "sentence": "He scorned their [[ingenuous diversions]], their innocent little amusements (he put it grandly).", "kor": "순진한 오락/소박한 놀이거리", "eng": "innocent amusements (mock-formal)"}, {"page": "84", "word": "changelings", "sentence": "He treated them like [[changelings]], odd creatures swapped in by fairies.", "kor": "바꿔치기된 아이/요정이 바꿔놓은 아이", "eng": "children secretly swapped by fairies"}, {"page": "84", "word": "siblings", "sentence": "She and Jem were [[siblings]], brother and sister.", "kor": "형제자매", "eng": "brothers and sisters"}, {"page": "84", "word": "harbored", "sentence": "He [[harbored]] strange ideas, keeping them tucked away in his mind.", "kor": "품다/마음에 간직하다", "eng": "held in the mind; entertained"}, {"page": "84", "word": "mystical notions", "sentence": "He had [[mystical notions]], lofty, otherworldly ideas about life.", "kor": "신비로운 생각들/신비주의적 개념들", "eng": "mystical, lofty ideas"}, {"page":