 sure as anything (dialect idiom)"}, {"page": "89", "word": "emerge", "sentence": "She waited for him to [[emerge]], to come back into view.", "kor": "나타나다/나오다", "eng": "to come out into view"}, {"page": "89", "word": "tentatively", "sentence": "He stepped out [[tentatively]], hesitantly, half afraid.", "kor": "조심스럽게/망설이며", "eng": "hesitantly; cautiously"}, {"page": "89", "word": "speak of", "sentence": "There was nothing to [[speak of]], nothing much worth mentioning.", "kor": "별것 아니다/딱히 없다", "eng": "nothing worth mentioning"}, {"page": "90", "word": "too quick on the draw", "sentence": "She was [[too quick on the draw]], too fast to throw the first punch (a gunfighter's phrase).", "kor": "너무 빨리 행동하다/먼저 치다", "eng": "too quick to attack (gunfighter idiom)"}, {"page": "90", "word": "shot back", "sentence": "Francis [[shot back]] into the house, darting back inside.", "kor": "재빨리 물러나다/쏘듯 달려가다", "eng": "darted back quickly"}, {"page": "90", "word": "retired to", "sentence": "He [[retired to]] the kitchen, withdrawing there for safety.", "kor": "물러나다/돌아가다", "eng": "withdrew to"}, {"page": "90", "word": "got me in here", "sentence": "\"Look what you [[got me in here]] for,\" she fumed — trapped me in this corner.", "kor": "나를 여기 가두다", "eng": "trapped me in here"}, {"page": "90", "word": "fussing", "sentence": "They were [[fussing]] again, squabbling and bickering.", "kor": "다투다/옥신각신하다", "eng": "quarrelling; squabbling"}, {"page": "90", "word": "back-porch listener", "sentence": "Francis was a [[back-porch listener]], an eavesdropper lurking at the porch.", "kor": "뒤 베란다에서 엿듣는 사람", "eng": "an eavesdropper at the back porch"}, {"page": "90", "word": "fool with me", "sentence": "\"Don't [[fool with me]],\" she warned — don't mess with me (dialect).", "kor": "나를 가지고 놀지 마라/건드리지 마라", "eng": "don't mess with me (dialect)"}, {"page": "90", "word": "tufts of grass", "sentence": "She tore up [[tufts of grass]], yanking clumps of it in her fury.", "kor": "풀 덩어리들", "eng": "clumps of grass"}, {"page": "90", "word": "got told", "sentence": "\"I [[got told]] off,\" she muttered — got a good scolding (dialect).", "kor": "혼났다/야단맞았다", "eng": "got scolded (dialect)"}, {"page": "90", "word": "botherin'", "sentence": "\"Quit [[botherin']] me,\" he whined — pestering me (dialect).", "kor": "귀찮게 하다/방해하다", "eng": "bothering; pestering (dialect)"}, {"page": "90", "word": "sufficiently subdued", "sentence": "When he was [[sufficiently subdued]], thoroughly cowed and quiet, she let go.", "kor": "충분히 제압된/충분히 조용해진", "eng": "thoroughly subdued and quiet"}, {"page": "90", "word": "crooned", "sentence": "Francis [[crooned]] the insult, sing-songing it softly to needle her.", "kor": "나지막이 노래하듯 말하다/부드럽게 읊조리다", "eng": "said in a soft sing-song"}, {"page": "90", "word": "split my knuckle to the bone", "sentence": "She had [[split my knuckle to the bone]], laying the skin open to the bone.", "kor": "뼈까지 손가락 관절을 찢다", "eng": "split the knuckle skin open to the bone"}, {"page": "90", "word": "impaired", "sentence": "Her fist was [[impaired]], its power weakened by the cut.", "kor": "손상된/약해진", "eng": "weakened; damaged"}, {"page": "90", "word": "sailed in with", "sentence": "She [[sailed in with]] her left, charging in swinging.", "kor": "달려들다/돌진하다", "eng": "charged in swinging"}, {"page": "90", "word": "pinned my arms to my sides", "sentence": "Uncle Jack [[pinned my arms to my sides]], clamping them tight against her body.", "kor": "팔을 옆구리에 꼼짝 못하게 하다", "eng": "clamped my arms against my body"}, {"page": "90", "word": "ministered to", "sentence": "Aunt Alexandra [[ministered to]] Francis, fussing and tending over him.", "kor": "보살피다/돌보다", "eng": "tended; cared for (mock-formal)"}, {"page": "90", "word": "bawled", "sentence": "Francis [[bawled]] at the top of his lungs, howling and crying loudly.", "kor": "울부짖다/엉엉 울다", "eng": "cried loudly; howled"}, {"page": "91", "word": "whore-lady", "sentence": "He had called Atticus a [[whore-lady]]'s lawyer — the ugly insult Scout had overheard about the trial.", "kor": "창녀 - 스카웃이 들은 욕설", "eng": "a word for a prostitute (Scout's overheard insult)"}, {"page": "91", "word": "features", "sentence": "His [[features]] twisted with rage, every part of his face.", "kor": "얼굴의 특징들/이목구비", "eng": "the parts of the face"}, {"page": "91", "word": "debating", "sentence": "Uncle Jack stood [[debating]] it, weighing what to do.", "kor": "고민하다/논쟁하다", "eng": "weighing a decision"}, {"page": "91", "word": "tarried in indecision", "sentence": "He [[tarried in indecision]], lingering, unable to make up his mind.", "kor": "우유부단하게 머뭇거리다/망설이며 지체하다", "eng": "lingered, unable to decide (formal)"}, {"page": "91", "word": "despise", "sentence": "She had come to [[despise]] Francis, to scorn and loathe him.", "kor": "경멸하다/혐오하다", "eng": "to scorn; loathe"}, {"page": "91", "word": "had it coming", "sentence": "He [[had it coming]], richly deserved the licking he got.", "kor": "당연히 받아야 할 것을 받다/자업자득", "eng": "deserved what he got"}, {"page": "91", "word": "high time", "sentence": "It was [[high time]] somebody hit him, long overdue.", "kor": "벌써 때가 되었다/진즉에 했어야 할", "eng": "long overdue"}, {"page": "91", "word": "surveyed the damage", "sentence": "Uncle Jack [[surveyed the damage]], inspecting her cut hand.", "kor": "피해를 살피다/상처를 확인하다", "eng": "examined the injuries"}, {"page": "91", "word": "reflecting upon", "sentence": "She lay [[reflecting upon]] it, thinking it over carefully.", "kor": "곰씹다/되새기다", "eng": "thinking carefully about"}, {"page": "91", "word": "relativity", "sentence": "It came back to [[relativity]] again, to how things compare in scale.", "kor": "상대성/상대적인 것", "eng": "how things compare in scale"}, {"page": "91", "word": "lick", "sentence": "She would take her [[lick]], her whipping, without complaint (dialect).", "kor": "때리다/혼내주다", "eng": "a beating (dialect)"}, {"page": "91", "word": "retreated to", "sentence": "She [[retreated to]] her room, withdrawing there to sulk.", "kor": "물러나다/후퇴하다", "eng": "withdrew 