e": "92", "word": "provocated", "sentence": "\"He [[provocated]] me,\" she insisted — her own made-up word for 'provoked.'", "kor": "자극하다/도발하다 - 방언/잘못된 문법", "eng": "provoked (Scout's invented grammar)"}, {"page": "92", "word": "knock his block off", "sentence": "She had wanted to [[knock his block off]], to clobber him hard on the head (idiom).", "kor": "머리를 날려버리다/세게 때리다", "eng": "hit him hard in the head (idiom)"}, {"page": "92", "word": "scratched his head", "sentence": "Uncle Jack [[scratched his head]], puzzling over her story.", "kor": "머리를 긁다", "eng": "scratched his head (in puzzlement)"}, {"page": "92", "word": "take it off him", "sentence": "Why should she [[take it off him]], put up with such insults from him?", "kor": "그것을 참다/받아들이다", "eng": "put up with it from him"}, {"page": "92", "word": "ruination", "sentence": "It was the [[ruination]] of the family, its downfall (he said grandly).", "kor": "파멸/몰락", "eng": "ruin; downfall (mock-grand)"}, {"page": "92", "word": "in for it", "sentence": "Francis was [[in for it]] now, about to catch real trouble.", "kor": "혼날 것 같다/큰일 났다", "eng": "about to be in trouble"}, {"page": "92", "word": "a good mind to", "sentence": "She had [[a good mind to]] hit him again, was strongly tempted.", "kor": "마음이 굳게 먹어지다/~하고 싶다", "eng": "strongly inclined to"}, {"page": "92", "word": "let it go", "sentence": "She decided to [[let it go]], to drop the matter.", "kor": "그냥 넘어가다/용서하다", "eng": "let the matter drop"}, {"page": "92", "word": "no intention of", "sentence": "She had [[no intention of]] explaining, no plan to at all.", "kor": "전혀 ~할 생각이 없다", "eng": "have no plan at all to"}, {"page": "92", "word": "wait'll I get my hands on", "sentence": "\"[[Wait'll I get my hands on]] you,\" she muttered at Francis — just wait till I catch you (dialect).", "kor": "내 손에 잡히기만 해봐라", "eng": "just wait till I catch (dialect threat)"}, {"page": "92", "word": "ruther", "sentence": "\"I'd [[ruther]] not say,\" she mumbled — 'rather' (dialect).", 