 "kor": "기다리고 있다/앞으로 닥칠", "eng": "waiting ahead for"}, {"page": "94", "word": "coming along", "sentence": "She was [[coming along]], slowly making progress.", "kor": "발전하다/잘 되어가다", "eng": "developing; making progress"}, {"page": "94", "word": "laid a hand on", "sentence": "He had never once [[laid a hand on]] her, never struck or spanked her.", "kor": "손을 대다/체벌하다", "eng": "struck; spanked"}, {"page": "94", "word": "get by with", "sentence": "It was the only way to [[get by with]] her, to manage and get through to her.", "kor": "넘기다/해나가다", "eng": "manage; get through"}, {"page": "94", "word": "minds me", "sentence": "\"She [[minds me]] half the time,\" he admitted — obeys me (dialect).", "kor": "말을 듣다/복종하다", "eng": "obeys me (dialect)"}, {"page": "94", "word": "Doesn't come up to scratch", "sentence": "\"[[Doesn't come up to scratch]],\" he sighed — falls short of the mark (idiom).", "kor": "기준에 미치지 못하다/제대로 해내지 못하다", "eng": "fails to meet the standard (idiom)"}, {"page": "94", "word": "keeping his head", "sentence": "[[Keeping his head]] was the trick, staying calm under fire.", "kor": "냉정을 유지하다", "eng": "staying calm under pressure"}, {"page": "94", "word": "just as soon", "sentence": "He would [[just as soon]] she learned it from him, would honestly prefer that.", "kor": "차라리/오히려", "eng": "would prefer to (dialect)"}, {"page": "94", "word": "pride's at stake", "sentence": "His [[pride's at stake]], his self-respect is on the line.", "kor": "자존심이 걸려 있다", "eng": "his pride is on the line"}, {"page": "94", "word": "evidence boils down to", "sentence": "The [[evidence boils down to]] one man's word against another's, reducing to just that.", "kor": "증거가 결국 ~으로 귀결되다", "eng": "the evidence reduces to"}, {"page": "94", "word": "jury", "sentence": "The [[jury]] would decide, the citizens who weigh the verdict.", "kor": "배심원단", "eng": "the citizens who decide the verdict"}, {"page": "94", "word": "acquainted with", "sentence": "The town was [[acquainted with]] the family, well familiar with them.", "kor": "알다/~와 면식이 있다", "eng": "familiar with; known to"}, {"page": "94", "word": "a generation off", "sentence": "Their thinking was [[a generation off]], a full generation behind the times.", "kor": "한 세대가 지났다/한 세대가 틀리다", "eng": "a generation behind the times"}, {"page": "94", "word": "jar the jury", "sentence": "He hoped to [[jar the jury]], to shake their easy certainty.", "kor": "배심원단을 흔들다/충격을 주다", "eng": "shake the jury's certainty"}, {"page": "94", "word": "appeal", "sentence": "He could file an [[appeal]], asking a higher court to review it.", "kor": "항소", "eng": "a request to a higher court"}, {"page": "94", "word": "get through life", "sentence": "She'd need it to [[get through life]], to make it through the years ahead.", "kor": "삶을 헤쳐나가다", "eng": "make it through life"}, {"page": "94", "word": "You're It", "sentence": "\"[[You're It]],\" fate seemed to say — you're the one chosen, as in a game of tag.", "kor": "네가 담당이야/네 차례야", "eng": "you're the one chosen (tag-game phrase)"}, {"page": "94", "word": "Let this cup pass from you, eh?", "sentence": "\"[[Let this cup pass from you, eh?]]\" Jack murmured — quoting the Bible's plea to be spared a hard trial.", "kor": "이 잔을 내게서 지나가게 하소서 - 성경 인용/어려운 일을 피하고 싶다", "eng": "spare me this suffering (Gethsemane allusion)"}, {"page": "94", "word": "face my children", "sentence": "\"I couldn't [[face my children]] otherwise,\" he said — couldn't look them in the eye.", "kor": "아이들을 대면하다/아이들 앞에 떳떳하다", "eng": "look my children in the eye"}, {"page": "94", "word": "without bitterness", "sentence": "He took it [[without bitterness]], with no resentment at all.", "kor": "원한 없이/씁쓸함 없이", "eng": "without resentment"}, {"page": "94", "word": "catching Maycomb's usual disease", "sentence": "He feared the children [[catching Maycomb's usual disease]], the town's old sickness of racial prejudice.", "kor": "메이컴의 통상적인 병에 걸리다 - 인종차별적 편견을 가리킴", "eng": "catching Maycomb's usual disease (racial prejudice)"}, {"pag