wn age.", "kor": "동년배들/같은 시대 사람들", "eng": "people of the same age"}, {"page": "96", "word": "crazy", "sentence": "Other fathers were [[crazy]] about football, wildly mad for it.", "kor": "열광적인/미친 듯이 좋아하는", "eng": "wildly enthusiastic about"}, {"page": "96", "word": "keep-away", "sentence": "They played [[keep-away]], the game of keeping the ball from the other side.", "kor": "공 뺏기 놀이", "eng": "a ball game of keeping the ball away"}, {"page": "96", "word": "tackle", "sentence": "Atticus wouldn't [[tackle]] anyone, wouldn't bring a player crashing down.", "kor": "태클하다/몸으로 막다", "eng": "to bring a player down (football)"}, {"page": "96", "word": "arouse the admiration", "sentence": "Nothing he did would [[arouse the admiration]] of anyone, win their admiring notice.", "kor": "감탄을 불러일으키다", "eng": "to win admiring attention"}, {"page": "96", "word": "tribal curse", "sentence": "Wearing glasses was the family's [[tribal curse]], the affliction that ran in their blood (she said grandly).", "kor": "[츄라이블] 집안의 저주/부족의 저주", "eng": "the curse running in the family (mock-grand)"}, {"page": "96", "word": "attributes", "sentence": "He had no exciting [[attributes]], no thrilling qualities at all.", "kor": "특성들/자질들", "eng": "qualities; characteristics"}, {"page": "96", "word": "inconspicuous", "sentence": "His job was [[inconspicuous]], quiet work that drew no attention.", "kor": "눈에 띄지 않는/두드러지지 않는", "eng": "not attracting attention"}, {"page": "96", "word": "buzzed with talk", "sentence": "The town [[buzzed with talk]], humming with gossip about the case.", "kor": "이야기로 윙윙거리다/소문이 돌다", "eng": "hummed with gossip"}, {"page": "96", "word": "complimentary", "sentence": "None of it was [[complimentary]], not a word of it flattering.", "kor": "칭찬하는/호의적인", "eng": "flattering; praising"}, {"page": "96", "word": "bout", "sentence": "After her [[bout]] with Francis, that one round of fighting, she had promised to quit.", "kor": "[바우ㅌ]한판/한 차례", "eng": "a round (of fighting)"}, {"page": "96", 