ness.", "kor": "은은한 우울함", "eng": "a soft, quiet sadness"}, {"page": "135", "word": "descends", "sentence": "Sunday calm [[descends]] on the house, settling down over it.", "kor": "내려앉다/드리우다", "eng": "comes down and settles over"}, {"page": "135", "word": "dispelled", "sentence": "Her arrival [[dispelled]] the peace, driving it clean away.", "kor": "사라지다/걷히다", "eng": "driven away; made to vanish"}, {"page": "135", "word": "dignity", "sentence": "She carried herself with [[dignity]], a composed, self-respecting bearing.", "kor": "체면/위엄", "eng": "self-respect; composed bearing"}, {"page": "135", "word": "vague dry kiss", "sentence": "She gave a [[vague dry kiss]], an absent, unloving peck.", "kor": "건성으로 하는 가벼운 키스", "eng": "an absent-minded, unromantic kiss"}, {"page": "135", "word": "affirmative", "sentence": "He nodded in the [[affirmative]], signalling yes (formal).", "kor": "긍정적으로/그렇다고", "eng": "saying yes (formal)"}, {"page": "135", "word": "shinny", "sentence": "The men brewed [[shinny]], the harsh home-made whiskey (slang).", "kor": "밀주/독한 자가 양조 술", "eng": "illegal home-made whiskey (slang)"}, {"page": "135", "word": "tight", "sentence": "He'd got [[tight]], slightly drunk (slang).", "kor": "술기운이 오른/약간 취한", "eng": "slightly drunk (slang)"}, {"page": "136", "word": "Missionary Society", "sentence": "She hosted the [[Missionary Society]], the church ladies' mission group.", "kor": "선교회", "eng": "a church ladies' group supporting missionaries"}, {"page": "136", "word": "hostess", "sentence": "She was the [[hostess]], the lady entertaining the guests.", "kor": "여주인/파티를 주최하는 여성", "eng": "a woman who entertains guests"}, {"page": "136", "word": "delicacies", "sentence": "She served [[delicacies]], fine and special foods.", "kor": "고급 음식/특별한 음식", "eng": "fine, special foods"}, {"page": "136", "word": "sustain", "sentence": "It would [[sustain]] them, keep them going through the long meeting.", "kor": "유지하다/버티게 하다", "eng": "to keep going; support through an ordeal"}, {"