 advise, caution, and warn]], the four favourite verbs of a born meddler.", "kor": "일정을 정리하고, 조언하며, 주의를 주고, 경고하곤 했다 – 오지랍쟁이고만 ㅎ", "eng": "the four verbs of a born meddler"}, {"page": "136", "word": "To all parties present and participating in the life of the county", "sentence": "She offered counsel \"[[To all parties present and participating in the life of the county]]\" — mock-legal talk for 'to everyone in town.'", "kor": "'지역 사회의 생활에 참여하고 있는 현존하는 모든 당사자들에게'라는 법률 문서풍 관용구", "eng": "mock-legal phrasing for 'to everyone in town'"}, {"page": "137", "word": "point out", "sentence": "She'd [[point out]] our faults, drawing sharp attention to them.", "kor": "짚어내다", "eng": "to draw attention to"}, {"page": "137", "word": "shortcomings", "sentence": "She catalogued our [[shortcomings]], our every fault and failing.", "kor": "단점/결점", "eng": "faults; weaknesses"}, {"page": "137", "word": "underlining the moral", "sentence": "She told tales [[underlining the moral]], driving home the lesson each time.", "kor": "교훈을 강조하며", "eng": "emphasizing the lesson"}, {"page": "137", "word": "morbid streak", "sentence": "We had a [[morbid streak]], an inherited dark, gloomy tendency, she said.", "kor": "병적인 기질/어두운 성향", "eng": "an inherited dark, gloomy tendency"}, {"page": "137", "word": "Streak", "sentence": "Every family had its [[Streak]], its supposed inherited trait.", "kor": "기질/성향", "eng": "a supposed inherited family trait"}, {"page": "137", "word": "mind other people's business", "sentence": "Her gift was to [[mind other people's business]], to meddle in everyone's affairs.", "kor": "남의 일에 참견하다", "eng": "to meddle in others' affairs"}, {"page": "137", "word": "hereditary", "sentence": "She thought it [[hereditary]], passed down through the blood.", "kor": "[허**뤠**더테리] 유전적인", "eng": "passed down through the family"}, {"page": "137", "word": "small hands and feet", "sentence": "Some had [[small hands and feet]], the joking sign of cousins marrying cousins.", "kor": "작은 손발 — 근친결혼의 결과라는 농담", "eng": "the joke result of cousins marrying cousins"}, {"page": "137", "word": "scratch most folks in Maycomb and they're kin to us", "sentence": "[[Scratch most folks in Maycomb and they're kin to us]] — dig a little and nearly everyone turns out a relative.", "kor": "메이콤 사람 대부분을 파고들면 우리 친척이다 — 마을이 워낙 좁아 다 연결되어 있다는 뜻", "eng": "dig a little and most locals are our relatives"}, {"page": "137", "word": "flighty", "sentence": "One cousin was [[flighty]], silly and scatterbrained.", "kor": "[플라이티] 변덕스러운/경솔한", "eng": "silly and unreliable; scatterbrained"}, {"page": "137", "word": "Incestuous Streak", "sentence": "Atticus teased about an [[Incestuous Streak]], a family habit of marrying relatives (a barbed joke).", "kor": "[인세스츄어ㅅ] 근친상간의 기질", "eng": "a family tendency to marry relatives (Atticus's barbed joke)"}, {"page": "138", "word": "preoccupation", "sentence": "Heredity was her [[preoccupation]], the obsession that filled her mind.", "kor": "집착/몰두", "eng": "an obsession; constant mental focus"}, {"page": "138", "word": "heredity", "sentence": "She believed in [[heredity]], the passing of nature through the blood.", "kor": "[허**뤠**디티] 유전/혈통", "eng": "the passing of traits through blood"}, {"page": "138", "word": "obliquely expressed", "sentence": "It was [[obliquely expressed]], hinted at, never said outright.", "kor": "간접적으로 표현된", "eng": "stated indirectly, never outright"}, {"page": "138", "word": "squatting on", "sentence": "A family's worth came from [[squatting on]] the same land for ages, settling there.", "kor": "자리잡고 살아온", "eng": "having lived settled on (land)"}, {"page": "138", "word": "tribe", "sentence": "The Finches were a [[tribe]], a whole clan of kin.", "kor": "무리/집안", "eng": "a clan; an extended family group"}, {"page": "138", "word": "brethren", "sentence": "His [[brethren]] gathered, his brothers and fellow kinsmen (an old word).", "kor": "형제들/같은 무리", "eng": "brothers; fellow members (archaic)"}, {"page": "138", "word": "thrived on", "sentence": "The Ewells [[thrived on]] relief, living comfortably off welfare money.", "kor": "덕분에 잘 살아온", "eng": "lived comfortably off"}, {"page": "138", "word": "welfare money", "sentence": "They took [[welfare money]], the government's relief payments.", "kor": "복지 지원금", "eng": "government relief payments"}, {"page": "138", "word": "awkwardly inland", "sentence": "Their land lay [[awkwardly inland]], far from the river and hard to reach.", "kor": "불편하게 내륙에 위치한", "eng": "inconveniently far from the river"}, {"page": "138", "word": "nimble-wittedness", "sentence": "The first Finch had [[nimble-wittedness]], a quick, cunning cleverness.", "kor": "재치/영리함, 재빠르게 상황을 파악하고 자신에게 유리하게 이용하는 능력", "eng": "quick, cunning cleverness"}, {"page": "138", "word": "dawn of history", "sentence": "Back at the [[dawn of history]], in the very earliest days.", "kor": "역사의 여명기/아주 오래전", "eng": "the very earliest times"}, {"page": "138", "word": "tavern", "sentence": "He kept a [[tavern]], an old roadside inn serving drink.", "kor": "[태벌ㄴ]선술집/주막", "eng": "an inn serving drink (dated)"}, {"page": "138", "word": "patriot", "sentence": "He was a [[patriot]], loyal to his new country.", "kor": "애국자", "eng": "a person loyal to their country"}, {"page": "138", "word": "ammunition", "sentence": "He stored [[ammunition]], bullets and powder.", "kor": "[애뮤니션] 탄약", "eng": "bullets and gunpowder"}, {"page": "138", "word": "domestic tranquility", "sentence": "He kept [[domestic tranquility]], peace and order within the land.", "kor": "국내 평화/지역 안정", "eng": "peace and order within the territory"}, {"page": "138", "word": "dispatched", "sentence": "The governor [[dispatched]] men, sending them off on official business.", "kor": "파견하다", "eng": "sent off on official business"}, {"page": "138", "word": "surveyors", "sentence": "He sent [[surveyors]], officials to measure and map the land.", "kor": "측량사", "eng": "officials who measure and map land"}, {"page": "138", "word": "establish its seat of government", 