]], the pouches slung over a saddle.", "kor": "안장 가방", "eng": "bags hung over a horse's saddle"}, {"page": "138", "word": "pig-trails", "sentence": "The first roads were [[pig-trails]], old animal paths worn into lanes.", "kor": "돼지 길 — 동물들이 다니던 길이 자연스럽게 도로가 된 곳", "eng": "animal paths that became the first roads"}, {"page": "139", "word": "grubbiness", "sentence": "A faint [[grubbiness]] marked them, a shabby, dirty look.", "kor": "지저분함/초라함", "eng": "shabby dirtiness"}, {"page": "139", "word": "distinguished", "sentence": "It [[distinguished]] the family, setting them apart from others.", "kor": "특징지었던", "eng": "set apart; marked as different"}, {"page": "139", "word": "proud", "sentence": "The bank stood [[proud]], grand and dignified.", "kor": "당당한/위엄 있는", "eng": "standing grand and dignified (of a building)"}, {"page": "139", "word": "deposited", "sentence": "He [[deposited]] his money, putting it in the bank.", "kor": "예금하다", "eng": "put (money) in a bank"}, {"page": "139", "word": "vetted", "sentence": "He had the mule [[vetted]], examined by the animal-doctor.", "kor": "수의사에게 진찰받다", "eng": "examined by a veterinarian"}, {"page": "139", "word": "ultimate wisdom", "sentence": "She questioned its [[ultimate wisdom]], whether it was truly wise in the end.", "kor": "궁극적인 지혜", "eng": "the final wisdom; whether it was truly wise"}, {"page": "139", "word": "maneuver", "sentence": "It was a clever [[maneuver]], a cunning little scheme.", "kor": "책략/술수", "eng": "a cunning scheme or move"}, {"page": "139", "word": "patchwork sea", "sentence": "Below lay a [[patchwork sea]], fields stitched together like a quilt.", "kor": "조각보 같은 바다/뒤섞인 풍경", "eng": "a landscape like stitched-together patches"}, {"page": "139", "word": "timberland", "sentence": "Much was [[timberland]], forest grown for lumber.", "kor": "삼림지", "eng": "forest land grown for timber"}, {"page": "140", "word": "War Between the States", "sentence": "Since the [[War Between the States]], the South's name for the Civil War, little had changed.", "kor": "남북전쟁", "eng": "the Southern name for the Civil War"}, {"page": "140", "word": "Reconstruction", "sentence": "Through [[Reconstruction]], the hard rebuilding years after the war, the town survived.", "kor": "재건시대 — 남북전쟁 후 남부 재건 시기", "eng": "the post-Civil-War rebuilding era (1865–77)"}, {"page": "140", "word": "inward", "sentence": "Maycomb turned [[inward]], folding in upon itself.", "kor": "안으로/내부적으로", "eng": "toward the inside (the town turned in on itself)"}, {"page": "140", "word": "faintly alike", "sentence": "The families looked [[faintly alike]], slightly resembling one another.", "kor": "어렴풋이 닮아 보이다", "eng": "slightly resembling one another"}, {"page": "140", "word": "ripple", "sentence": "It made no [[ripple]], not the smallest stir.", "kor": "잔물결/미미한 영향", "eng": "a tiny disturbance; a small effect"}, {"page": "140", "word": "family resemblance", "sentence": "There was a [[family resemblance]], the shared look of kin.", "kor": "가족 간의 닮음", "eng": "the shared look of related people"}, {"page": "140", "word": "caste system", "sentence": "The town had a [[caste system]], a rigid order fixed by birth.", "kor": "계급 제도", "eng": "a rigid social hierarchy by birth"}, {"page": "140", "word": "utterly", "sentence": "She believed it [[utterly]], completely and totally.", "kor": "완전하게", "eng": "completely; totally"}, {"page": "140", "word": "took for granted", "sentence": "Folks [[took for granted]] their places, accepting them without question.", "kor": "당연하게 받아들였다", "eng": "accepted without question"}, {"page": "140", "word": "character shadings", "sentence": "Each clan had its [[character shadings]], subtle shades of personality.", "kor": "성격의 미묘한 차이", "eng": "subtle shades of personality"}, {"page": "140", "word": "refined", "sentence": "These traits were [[refined]], polished over generations.", "kor": "다듬어진/정제된", "eng": "polished and perfected over time"}, {"page": "140", "word": "dicta", "sentence": "She quoted family [[d