": "The engine [[coughed]], sputtering to life.", "kor": "시동이 걸리다/기침하듯 소리를 내다", "eng": "(of engines) sputtered into life"}, {"page": "170", "word": "produced his handkerchief", "sentence": "Atticus [[produced his handkerchief]], drawing it out.", "kor": "손수건을 꺼내다", "eng": "took out his handkerchief"}, {"page": "170", "word": "going-over", "sentence": "He gave his face a [[going-over]], a thorough wipe.", "kor": "훑다/닦다", "eng": "a thorough wipe-down"}, {"page": "170", "word": "violently", "sentence": "He blew his nose [[violently]], with great force.", "kor": "세차게/격렬하게", "eng": "with great force"}, {"page": "170", "word": "husky", "sentence": "His voice was [[husky]], low and hoarse.", "kor": "허스키한/쉰", "eng": "low, rough, and hoarse (voice)"}, {"page": "170", "word": "crisply", "sentence": "She answered [[crisply]], sharp and clear.", "kor": "날카롭게/또렷하게", "eng": "sharply and clearly"}, {"page": "170", "word": "damn tootin'", "sentence": "\"[[Damn tootin']],\" the man agreed — slang for 'you're absolutely right.'", "kor": "당연하지/맞고말고 — 강한 동의를 나타내는 표현", "eng": "(slang) you're absolutely right"}, {"page": "170", "word": "covered", "sentence": "Mr. Underwood had them [[covered]], kept under his gun the whole time.", "kor": "엄호하다/지켜보다", "eng": "kept under the protection of a gun"}, {"page": "170", "word": "double-barreled shotgun", "sentence": "He held a [[double-barreled shotgun]], the two-barrelled kind.", "kor": "쌍발 엽총", "eng": "a shotgun with two barrels"}, {"page": "170", "word": "encumbered", "sentence": "Atticus was [[encumbered]], weighed down and hampered.", "kor": "[인컴버드] 짐을 진/방해받는", "eng": "weighed down; hampered by a burden"}, {"page": "170", "word": "giving him hell", "sentence": "Aunt Alexandra was [[giving him hell]], scolding him fiercely.", "kor": "혼내다/야단치다", "eng": "scolding him severely"}, {"page": "170", "word": "massaged", "sentence": "He [[massaged]] Jem's hair, rubbing it gently.", "kor": "쓰다듬다/가볍게 문지르다", "eng": "rubbed gently"}, {"page": "170", "word": "gesture of affection", "sentence": "It was a [[gesture of affection]], a tender show of love.", "kor": "애정의 표현/애정 어린 몸짓", "eng": "a physical expression of love"}], "16": [{"page": "171", "word": "coasted to the carhouse", "sentence": "Atticus [[coasted to the carhouse]], rolling into the garage with the engine switched off.", "kor": "시동을 끄고 천천히 차고까지 굴러가다", "eng": "rolled into the garage with the engine off"}, {"page": "171", "word": "hit me", "sentence": "It finally [[hit me]], the danger of the night sinking in with full force.", "kor": "실감이 나다/깨닫다", "eng": "struck me with full force; finally sank in"}, {"page": "171", "word": "appetite", "sentence": "She had no [[appetite]], no desire to eat.", "kor": "식욕", "eng": "desire to eat"}, {"page": "171", "word": "delicate", "sentence": "Her stomach was [[delicate]], weak and easily upset.", "kor": "약한/입맛이 없는", "eng": "weak; easily upset (of an appetite)"}, {"page": "171", "word": "frank admiration", "sentence": "She looked at him with [[frank admiration]], open, undisguised awe.", "kor": "솔직한 감탄/노골적인 감탄", "eng": "open, undisguised admiration"}, {"page": "171", "word": "radiated waves of disapproval", "sentence": "Aunt Alexandra [[radiated waves of disapproval]], giving it off like heat from a stove.", "kor": "못마땅함의 파장을 내뿜다", "eng": "gave off disapproval like heat from a stove"}, {"page": "171", "word": "despises", "sentence": "She [[despises]] him, looking down with real contempt.", "kor": "경멸하다/몹시 싫어하다", "eng": "looks down on with contempt"}, {"page": "171", "word": "profane", "sentence": "Mr. Underwood was [[profane]], free with his swearing and irreverent.", "kor": "신성모독적인/상스러운", "eng": "given to swearing; irreverent"}, {"page": "171", "word": "fey fit of humor", "sentence": "In a [[fey fit of humor]], a strange whimsical mood, his parents named him oddly.", "kor": "기묘한 유머 발작", "eng": "a strange, whimsical burst of humor"}, {"page": "171", "word": "christened", "sentence": "He was [[christened]] Braxton, named so 