ne had [[blind spots]], ingrained prejudices they couldn't see past.", "kor": "맹점/편견으로 인해 보지 못하는 부분", "eng": "areas where a person simply cannot see clearly; ingrained prejudices"}, {"page": "173", "word": "conceded", "sentence": "Atticus [[conceded]] it, admitting it reluctantly.", "kor": "인정하다/양보하다", "eng": "admitted reluctantly"}, {"page": "173", "word": "gang of wild animals", "sentence": "A mob seems a [[gang of wild animals]], a pack of wild beasts.", "kor": "야수들의 무리", "eng": "a pack of wild beasts (what a mob seems to be)"}, {"page": "173", "word": "stand in my shoes", "sentence": "He could [[stand in my shoes]], seeing it from her position.", "kor": "내 입장이 되어보다", "eng": "to see things from my position; to empathize"}, {"page": "173", "word": "affirmed", "sentence": "Atticus [[affirmed]] it, declaring it firmly.", "kor": "단언하다/확언하다", "eng": "declared firmly"}, {"page": "173", "word": "flatly", "sentence": "He said it [[flatly]], in an absolute, level tone.", "kor": "단호하게/딱 잘라", "eng": "in a flat, absolute tone"}, {"page": "173", "word": "bearing a grudge", "sentence": "He wasn't [[bearing a grudge]], holding on to no resentment.", "kor": "원한을 품다/앙심을 갖다", "eng": "holding on to resentment"}, {"page": "174", "word": "bounding", "sentence": "Jem came [[bounding]] in, running with great leaps.", "kor": "깡충깡충 뛰어오다", "eng": "running with leaps and bounds"}, {"page": "174", "word": "nest", "sentence": "A [[nest]] of troublemakers gathered, a whole den of them.", "kor": "한 무리/소굴", "eng": "a den or cluster (of troublemakers)"}, {"page": "174", "word": "disorderly", "sentence": "They were [[disorderly]], rowdy and causing a disturbance.", "kor": "난동을 부리는/무질서한", "eng": "rowdy; causing disturbance"}, {"page": "174", "word": "leisurely", "sentence": "Folks came [[leisurely]], unhurried and relaxed.", "kor": "여유로운/느긋한", "eng": "unhurried; relaxed"}, {"page": "174", "word": "lurched by", "sentence": "A drunk [[lurched by]], swaying unsteadily past.", "kor": "비틀거리며 지나가다", "eng": "passed by swaying unsteadily"}, {"page": "174", "word": "thoroughbred", "sentence": "It moved like a [[thoroughbred]], a fine purebred horse.", "kor": "순종말/혈통 좋은 말", "eng": "a purebred horse"}, {"page": "174", "word": "'fore", "sentence": "\"[['fore]] you know it,\" he said — 'before' (dialect).", "kor": "before의 축약형", "eng": "(dialect) before"}, {"page": "174", "word": "wagonload", "sentence": "A whole [[wagonload]] arrived, a wagon full of people.", "kor": "마차 가득", "eng": "a full wagon's worth"}, {"page": "174", "word": "sunbonnets", "sentence": "Women wore [[sunbonnets]], wide cotton hats shading their faces.", "kor": "햇빛 가리개 모자", "eng": "wide-brimmed cotton hats shielding the face from sun"}, {"page": "174", "word": "Mennonites", "sentence": "The [[Mennonites]] came too, the plain-living Christian folk.", "kor": "[메노나이츠] 메노나이트 — 소박한 생활을 하는 기독교 공동체", "eng": "a plain-living Christian community descended from the Anabaptists"}, {"page": "174", "word": "initial", "sentence": "His name held one [[initial]], a single first letter.", "kor": "이니셜/성명의 첫 글자", "eng": "the first letter of a name"}, {"page": "175", "word": "clerk", "sentence": "The [[clerk]] kept the records, the court's record-keeping official.", "kor": "서기/법원 직원", "eng": "a court official who keeps records"}, {"page": "175", "word": "the county", "sentence": "All of [[the county]] turned out, the whole population of it.", "kor": "마을 사람들 (카운티 주민 전체)", "eng": "the people of the whole county"}, {"page": "175", "word": "attitudes", "sentence": "Each had their [[attitudes]], their settled ways of behaving.", "kor": "태도/성향", "eng": "characteristic ways of behaving"}, {"page": "175", "word": "prominent", "sentence": "The [[prominent]] families came, the well-known, standing-out ones.", "kor": "두드러진/저명한", "eng": "well-known; standing out"}, {"page": "175", "word": "straight Prohibition ticket", "sentence": "He voted a [[straight Prohibition ticket]], only for anti-liquor candidates.", "kor": "금주법 지지 후보에만 투표하다