from Proverbs: 'A merry heart maketh a cheerful countenance')"}, {"page": "175", "word": "foot-washers", "sentence": "The [[foot-washers]] came, the strict literal-minded Baptists.", "kor": "발 씻는 자들 — 극단적으로 엄격한 침례교 신자들", "eng": "strict primitive Baptists who take the Bible with total literalism"}, {"page": "176", "word": "objected to", "sentence": "They [[objected to]] flowers, frowning on them as sinful.", "kor": "반대하다", "eng": "disapproved of"}, {"page": "176", "word": "heightened", "sentence": "Her zeal was [[heightened]], grown more intense.", "kor": "고조된/더욱 강해진", "eng": "intensified"}, {"page": "176", "word": "formidable", "sentence": "Her grasp of Scripture was [[formidable]], impressively strong.", "kor": "대단한/인상적인", "eng": "impressively strong (her command of Scripture)"}, {"page": "176", "word": "strolled over", "sentence": "Mr. Avery [[strolled over]], walking up casually.", "kor": "어슬렁어슬렁 걸어오다", "eng": "walked over casually"}, {"page": "176", "word": "morbid", "sentence": "It was [[morbid]] curiosity, an unhealthy fixation on suffering.", "kor": "병적인/불건전한", "eng": "unhealthily focused on death and suffering"}, {"page": "176", "word": "Roman carnival", "sentence": "It became a [[Roman carnival]], a cruel public spectacle like Rome's games.", "kor": "로마의 카니발 — 구경거리로 전락한 재판", "eng": "a cruel public spectacle, like Rome's games where people watched others die for amusement"}, {"page": "176", "word": "William Jennings Bryan", "sentence": "Crowds gathered as for [[William Jennings Bryan]], the great orator who once drew thousands.", "kor": "윌리엄 제닝스 브라이언 — 미국의 유명 정치가·연설가", "eng": "a famous orator who drew enormous crowds; three-time presidential candidate"}, {"page": "176", "word": "inquired", "sentence": "Jem [[inquired]], asking the question.", "kor": "물어보다/묻다", "eng": "asked"}, {"page": "176", "word": "subpoena", "sentence": "She got a [[subpoena]], a legal order to appear in court.", "kor": "[서피나] 소환장", "eng": "a legal order to appear in court"}, {"page": "176", "word": "elucidate", "sentence": "Atticus would [[elucidate]] it, making it clear.", "kor": "설명하다/명확히 하다", "eng": "to explain; to make clear"}, {"page": "176", "word": "testify", "sentence": "She'd have to [[testify]], to give her evidence as a witness.", "kor": "증언하다", "eng": "to give evidence as a witness"}, {"page": "176", "word": "picking the jury", "sentence": "They were [[picking the jury]], choosing the twelve jurors.", "kor": "배심원단을 선발하다", "eng": "selecting the twelve jurors"}, {"page": "176", "word": "gala occasion", "sentence": "It was a [[gala occasion]], a festive event for the town.", "kor": "축제 같은/성대한 행사", "eng": "a festive event"}, {"page": "177", "word": "hitching rail", "sentence": "Mules lined the [[hitching rail]], the bar for tying them.", "kor": "말을 묶어두는 기둥/난간", "eng": "a rail for tying up horses and mules"}, {"page": "177", "word": "picnic parties", "sentence": "[[Picnic parties]] settled in, groups spreading out their meals.", "kor": "소풍 나온 무리들", "eng": "groups eating picnic meals"}, {"page": "177", "word": "washing down", "sentence": "They were [[washing down]] their food, swallowing it with a drink.", "kor": "음식을 음료로 넘기다", "eng": "swallowing food with the help of a drink"}, {"page": "177", "word": "affluent", "sentence": "The [[affluent]] folk had soda, the wealthy, well-off ones.", "kor": "부유한/풍족한", "eng": "wealthy; well-off"}, {"page": "177", "word": "bulb-shaped", "sentence": "They drank from [[bulb-shaped]] bottles, shaped like light bulbs.", "kor": "전구 모양의", "eng": "shaped like a light bulb"}, {"page": "177", "word": "greasy-faced", "sentence": "Children sat [[greasy-faced]], shiny from the greasy food.", "kor": "기름기 묻은 얼굴의", "eng": "with faces shiny from greasy food"}, {"page": "177", "word": "popped-the-whip", "sentence": "Boys [[popped-the-whip]], playing the game that flings the end child off.", "kor": "채찍놀이를 하다", "eng": "played crack-the-whip (a chain game that flings the end child)"}, {"page": "177", "word": "lunched at their mothers' breasts", "sentence": "Babies [[lunched at their mothers' breasts]], nursing as they fed.", "kor": "엄마 젖을 먹다", "eng": "nursed; were breast-fed"}, {"page": "177", "word": "sardines", "sentence": "Some ate [[sardines]], the little canned fish.", "kor": "정어리", "eng": "small canned fish"}, {"page": "177", "word": "crackers", "sentence": "And [[crackers]], plain dry biscuits.", "kor": "크래커", "eng": "plain dry biscuits"}, {"page": "177", "word": "vivid flavors", "sentence": "Those had [[vivid flavors]], sharp and strong.", "kor": "강렬한 맛", "eng": "sharp, strong flavors"}, {"page": "177", "word": "upset the ladies", "sentence": "It would [[upset the ladies]], offend their delicate sensibilities.", "kor": "숙녀들을 불편하게 하다", "eng": "to offend the ladies' sensibilities"}, {"page": "177", "word": "mixed chillun", "sentence": "He spoke of [[mixed chillun]], mixed-race children (dialect).", "kor": "혼혈 아이들", "eng": "(dialect) mixed-race children"}, {"page": "177", "word": "trash", "sentence": "They were called [[trash]], worthless low-class folk (a cruel label).", "kor": "쓰레기 같은 사람/하층민", "eng": "worthless low-class people (a cruel social label)"}, {"page": "177", "word": "riverbank", "sentence": "They lived by the [[riverbank]], the land along the river.", "kor": "강둑/강변", "eng": "the land along a river"}, {"page": "177", "word": "real old family", "sentence": "The Finches were a [[real old family]], one of long-established standing.", "kor": "유서 깊은 가문", "eng": "a family of long-established standing"}, {"page": "177", "word": "to boot", "sentence": "And respectable [[to boot]], on top of that besides.", "kor": "게다가/덤으로", "eng": "in addition; on top of that"}, {"page": "178", "word": "weddin'", "sentence": "\"At the [[weddin']],\" she began — wedding (dialect).", "kor": "결혼식", "eng": "(dialect) wedding"}, {"page": "178", "word": "rehearsal", "sentence": "There was a [[rehearsal]], a practice run of the ceremony.", "kor": "리허설/예행연습", "eng": "a practice run of the ceremony"}, {"page": "178", "word": "blew her head off", "sentence": "The bride [[blew her head off]], killing herself with a shotgun.", "kor": "머리에 총을 쏘아 자살하다", "eng": "killed herself with a shotgun"}, {"page": "178", "word": "reckoned", "sentence": "Folks [[reckoned]] it scandal, supposed and figured so.", "kor": "생각하다/여기다", "eng": "figured; supposed"}, {"page": "178", "word": "sorta drunk", "sentence": "He was [[sorta drunk]] always, somewhat tipsy all the time (dialect).", "kor": "약간/늘 취해 있는", "eng": "(dialect) somewhat drunk all the time"}, {"page": "178", "word": "red-kinky-headed", "sentence": "The children were [[red-kinky-headed]], with tight red curls.", "kor": "붉은 곱슬머리의", "eng": "with tightly curled red hair"}, {"page": "178", "word": "in-betweens", "sentence": "They were [[in-betweens]], belonging to neither world, caught between two.", "kor": "중간에 낀 사람들", "eng": "people belonging to neither side; caught between two worlds"}, {"page": "178", "word": "shipped", "sentence": "Some were [[shipped]] away, sent off to live elsewhere.", "kor": "보내다/이주시키다", "eng": "sent away (to live elsewhere)"}, {"page": "178", "word": "flaring nostrils", "sentence": "He had [[flaring nostrils]], wide and flared.", "kor": "벌름거리는 콧구멍", "eng": "wide, flared nostrils"}, {"page": "179", "word": "hafta", "sentence": "\"You'd [[hafta]] ask,\" she said — have to (dialect).", "kor": "have to의 구어체", "eng": "(dialect) have to"}, {"page": "179", "word": "Ethiopia", "sentence": "Trace it back to [[Ethiopia]], Uncle Jack said — ancestry traced far enough becomes unknowable.", "kor": "에티오피아", "eng": "Ethiopia — Uncle Jack's point that ancestry traced far enough is unknowable"}, {"page": "179", "word": "drop of Negro blood", "sentence": "A single [[drop of Negro blood]] marked you — the cruel 'one-drop rule' of the era.", "kor": "흑인의 피 한 방울 — '한 방울 규칙'", "eng": "the One Drop Rule: any Black ancestry at all classified a person as Black"}, {"page": "179", "word": "lunchers", "sentence": "The [[lunchers]] finished, the people who had been eating.", "kor": "점심을 먹는 사람들", "eng": "the people eating lunch"}, {"page": "179", "word": "scatter", "sentence": "They began to [[scatter]] crumbs, scattering them about.", "kor": "흩어지다/흩뿌리다", "eng": "to throw about in all directions"}, {"page": "179", "word": "cellophane", "sentence": "They balled up [[cellophane]], the clear plastic wrap.", "kor": "셀로판 포장지", "eng": "clear plastic wrapping"}, {"page": "179", "word": "cradled", "sentence": "Babies were [[cradled]] on hips, held gently there.", "kor": "안기다/포대기에 싸이다", "eng": "held gently (on hips)"}, {"page": "179", "word": "sweat-stained hats", "sentence": "Men wore [[sweat-stained hats]], marked dark with sweat.", "kor": "땀에 젖은 모자", "eng": "hats marked with sweat"}, {"page": "179", "word": "herded", "sentence": "They were [[herded]] along, driven like a flock.", "kor": "몰다/이끌다", "eng": "drove like a flock"}, {"page": "179", "word": "dusted their breeches", "sentence": "They [[dusted their breeches]], brushing the dirt off their trousers.", "kor": "바지의 먼지를 털다", "eng": "brushed the dust off their trousers"}, {"page": "179", "word": "dispel", "sentence": "Nothing could [[dispel]] the mood, drive it away.", "kor": "없애다/흩어버리다", "eng": "to drive away; to make vanish"}, {"page": "179", "word": "faintly reminiscent of", "sentence": "It was [[faintly reminiscent of]] a temple, slightly recalling one.", "kor": "희미하게 ~을 연상시키는", "eng": "slightly reminding one of"}, {"page": "179", "word": "pillars", "sentence": "Tall [[pillars]] held it up, the great columns.", "kor": "기둥", "eng": "columns"}, {"page": "179", "word": "burden", "sentence": "They bore the [[burden]], the heavy weight of the roof.", "kor": "부담/짐", "eng": "the load carried (here, the roof)"}, {"page": "180", "word": "early Victorian", "sentence": "It was [[early Victorian]], in that old architectural style.", "kor": "초기 빅토리아 시대 양식의", "eng": "in the architectural style of early Queen Victoria's reign"}, {"page": "180", "word": "unoffensive vista", "sentence": "It gave an [[unoffensive vista]], a plain, unremarkable view.", "kor": "거슬리지 않는 전경", "eng": "an inoffensive, unremarkable view"}, {"page": "180", "word": "Greek revival columns", "sentence": "It had [[Greek revival columns]], the classical pillars the old South loved.", "kor": "그리스 부흥 양식의 기둥들", "eng": "columns in the classical style beloved of the antebellum South"}, {"page": "180", "word": "clashed with", "sentence": "They [[clashed with]] the tower, jarring against it.", "kor": "충돌하다/어울리지 않다", "eng": "jarred against; did not match"}, {"page": "180", "word": "clock tower", "sentence": "A [[clock tower]] rose above, housing the town clock.", "kor": "시계탑", "eng": "a tower housing a clock"}, {"page": "180", "word": "rusty unreliable instrument", "sentence": "It held a [[rusty unreliable instrument]], a clock too rusted to trust.", "kor": "녹슬고 믿을 수 없는 시계", "eng": "a rusted clock that cannot be trusted"}, {"page": "180", "word": "determined to preserve every physical scrap of the past", "sentence": "The town was [[determined to preserve every physical scrap of the past]], keeping every last relic.", "kor": "과거의 모든 물리적 잔재를 보존하려는", "eng": "resolved to keep every last piece of what came before"}, {"page": "180", "word": "sundry", "sentence": "It held [[sundry]] offices, various assorted ones.", "kor": "[선드리] 여러 가지/다양한", "eng": "various; assorted"}, {"page": "180", "word": "sunless county cubbyholes", "sentence": "They were [[sunless county cubbyholes]], tiny windowless rooms.", "kor": "햇빛이 들지 않는 작은 사무실들", "eng": "tiny windowless county offices"}, {"page": "180", "word": "tax assessor", "sentence": "The [[tax assessor]] worked there, who values property for tax.", "kor": "세금 평가관", "eng": "the official who values property for taxation"}, {"page": "180", "word": "tax collector", "sentence": "And the [[tax collector]], who gathers in the taxes.", "kor": "세금 징수원", "eng": "the official who collects taxes"}, {"page": "180", "word": "county clerk", "sentence": "The [[county clerk]] kept records, the county's record-keeper.", "kor": "카운티 서기", "eng": "the county's record-keeping official"}, {"page": "180", "word": "county solicitor", "sentence": "The [[county solicitor]] prosecuted, the county's lawyer.", "kor": "[솔리시터] 카운티 검사", "eng": "the county prosecutor"}, {"page": "180", "word": "circuit clerk", "sentence": "The [[circuit clerk]] served the travelling court.", "kor": "순회 법원 서기", "eng": "the clerk of the traveling court"}, {"page": "180", "word": "judge of probate", "sentence": "The [[judge of probate]] ruled on wills and estates.", "kor": "유언 검인 판사", "eng": "the judge who handles wills and estates"}, {"page": "180", "word": "hutches", "sentence": "They worked in [[hutches]], cramped box-like rooms.", "kor": "작은 방/우리 같은 사무실", "eng": "cramped boxes of rooms (literally, rabbit cages)"}, {"page": "180", "word": "decaying record books", "sentence": "Shelves held [[decaying record books]], rotting with age.", "kor": "썩어가는 기록부", "eng": "record books rotting with age"}, {"page": "180", "word": "stale urine", "sentence": "It smelled of [[stale urine]], old and sour.", "kor": "오래된 소변 냄새", "eng": "the smell of old urine"}, {"page": "180", "word": "film of dust", "sentence": "A [[film of dust]] covered all, a thin coating.", "kor": "먼지 막/얇은 먼지 층", "eng": "a thin coating of dust"}, {"page": "180", "word": "floorboards", "sentence": "It lay on the [[floorboards]], the wooden floor-planks.", "kor": "마루판/바닥 판자", "eng": "the wooden boards of the floor"}, {"page": "180", "word": "creatures of their environment", "sentence": "The clerks were [[creatures of their environment]], shaped wholly by their surroundings.", "kor": "그 환경의 창조물", "eng": "beings shaped entirely by their surroundings"}, {"page": "180", "word": "gray-faced", "sentence": "They were [[gray-faced]], ashen and colorless.", "kor": "창백한/잿빛 얼굴의", "eng": "with ashen, colorless faces"}, {"page": "180", "word": "untouched by wind or sun", "sentence": "They seemed [[untouched by wind or sun]], cut off from the outdoors.", "kor": "바람도 햇빛도 닿지 않은", "eng": "never exposed to the outdoors; cut off from the living world"}, {"page": "180", "word": "bargained for", "sentence": "More came than they'd [[bargained for]], than they had expected.", "kor": "예상하다/각오하다", "eng": "expected; were prepared for"}, {"page": "180", "word": "multitudes", "sentence": "[[Multitudes]] poured in, vast crowds of them.", "kor": "군중/수많은 사람들", "eng": "huge crowds"}, {"page": "180", "word": "stairwell", "sentence": "They jammed the [[stairwell]], the staircase shaft.", "kor": "계단통", "eng": "the shaft containing the staircase"}, {"page": "180", "word": "Idlers' Club", "sentence": "The [[Idlers' Club]] gathered, the old men who watch court for sport.", "kor": "빈둥거리는 노인들의 모임", "eng": "the informal club of old men who watch court for entertainment"}, {"page": "180", "word": "unobtrusive", "sentence": "They were [[unobtrusive]], drawing no attention.", "kor": "눈에 띄지 않는", "eng": "not attracting attention"}, {"page": "180", "word": "suspendered", "sentence": "They were [[suspendered]], wearing their braces.", "kor": "멜빵을 맨", "eng": "wearing suspenders"}, {"page": "181", "word": "twilight days", "sentence": "In their [[twilight days]], the closing years of life.", "kor": "황혼기/노년기", "eng": "the closing years of life"}, {"page": "181", "word": "attentive critics", "sentence": "They were [[attentive critics]], watchful judges of the court's doings.", "kor": "주의 깊은 비평가들", "eng": "careful, watchful judges (of courthouse business)"}, {"page": "181", "word": "Chief Justice", "sentence": "He knew as much as the [[Chief Justice]], the Supreme Court's head judge.", "kor": "대법원장", "eng": "the head judge of the Supreme Court"}, {"page": "181", "word": "spectators", "sentence": "The [[spectators]] crowded in, the folk come to watch.", "kor": "구경꾼/방청객", "eng": "people watching"}, {"page": "181", "word": "resentful", "sentence": "They were [[resentful]] of change, bitter at any disturbanc