usly racist term) the Black settlement nearby"}, {"page": "196", "word": "devaluin'", "sentence": "It was [[devaluin']] his land, lowering its worth (dialect).", "kor": "가치를 떨어뜨리다", "eng": "(dialect) lowering the value of"}, {"page": "196", "word": "hasty descent from the stand", "sentence": "He made a [[hasty descent from the stand]], a hurried climb down.", "kor": "[헤이스티] 서둘러 증인석에서 내려옴", "eng": "a hurried climb down from the stand"}, {"page": "196", "word": "smack into", "sentence": "He ran [[smack into]] Atticus, colliding straight into him.", "kor": "정면으로 부딪히다", "eng": "collided straight into"}, {"page": "196", "word": "genially", "sentence": "Atticus stepped aside [[genially]], in a warm, good-humoured way.", "kor": "[지니얼리] 친절하게/상냥하게", "eng": "in a warm, good-humored way"}, {"page": "196", "word": "haughty suspicion", "sentence": "Ewell eyed him with [[haughty suspicion]], arrogant distrust.", "kor": "[호티] 오만한 불신", "eng": "arrogant distrust"}, {"page": "196", "word": "confronted by opposing counsel", "sentence": "[[Confronted by opposing counsel]], facing the other side's lawyer, he bristled.", "kor": "상대측 변호인과 맞닥뜨려", "eng": "facing the other side's lawyer"}, {"page": "197", "word": "nature of her injuries", "sentence": "He asked the [[nature of her injuries]], what they were like.", "kor": "부상의 성격/정도", "eng": "what her injuries were like"}, {"page": "197", "word": "warranted immediate medical attention", "sentence": "They hadn't [[warranted immediate medical attention]], hadn't called for a doctor at once.", "kor": "즉각적인 치료를 요한다", "eng": "called for a doctor at once"}, {"page": "197", "word": "sheriff's testimony", "sentence": "It matched the [[sheriff's testimony]], what Tate had said.", "kor": "보안관의 증언", "eng": "what the sheriff said on the stand"}, {"page": "197", "word": "considered the matter carefully", "sentence": "Ewell [[considered the matter carefully]], thinking it over warily.", "kor": "신중히 따져보다", "eng": "thought it over warily"}, {"page": "197", "