: "262", "word": "right then and there", "sentence": "She decided [[right then and there]], on the spot.", "kor": "그 자리에서 즉시", "eng": "immediately, on the spot"}, {"page": "262", "word": "piety", "sentence": "She showed great [[piety]], devout reverence.", "kor": "경건/신심", "eng": "devout religious reverence"}, {"page": "263", "word": "sin and squalor", "sentence": "She spoke of [[sin and squalor]], wrongdoing and filth.", "kor": "죄악과 불결함", "eng": "moral wrongdoing and filthy living conditions"}, {"page": "263", "word": "turned on her chimes", "sentence": "She [[turned on her chimes]], her artificially sweet voice.", "kor": "종소리 같은 목소리를 (가식적으로) 내다", "eng": "switched on an artificially sweet, musical voice"}, {"page": "263", "word": "forgive and forget", "sentence": "Christians should [[forgive and forget]], pardon and move on (idiom).", "kor": "용서하고 잊다", "eng": "(idiom) pardon a wrong and stop dwelling on it"}, {"page": "263", "word": "lead a Christian life", "sentence": "They should [[lead a Christian life]], by Christian morals.", "kor": "기독교적인 삶을 살다", "eng": "to live according to Christian morals"}, {"page": "263", "word": "from here on out", "sentence": "[[From here on out]], from now on, she'd try.", "kor": "이제부터는/앞으로는", "eng": "from now on"}, {"page": "263", "word": "see it my way", "sentence": "Folks would [[see it my way]], agree with her view.", "kor": "내 의견에 동의하다", "eng": "agree with my view"}, {"page": "263", "word": "blow over", "sentence": "It would [[blow over]], pass and be forgotten (idiom).", "kor": "(소동 등이) 지나가다/잠잠해지다", "eng": "(idiom) pass and be forgotten, like a storm"}, {"page": "263", "word": "subservient", "sentence": "She wanted them [[subservient]], submissively obedient.", "kor": "종속적인/복종하는", "eng": "submissively obedient"}, {"page": "263", "word": "devastating", "sentence": "It was a [[devastating]] remark, crushing.", "kor": "엄청난 충격을 주는/파괴적인", "eng": "causing overwhelming shock or damage"}, {"page": "263", "word": "assume a different tone of voice", "sentence": "She'd [[assume a different tone of voice]], changing her manner of speaking.", "kor": "다른 목소리 톤을 취하다", "eng": "adopt a changed manner of speaking"}, {"page": "263", "word": "stately largo", "sentence": "She spoke in a [[stately largo]], slow and dignified.", "kor": "위엄 있고 느릿느릿하게", "eng": "slow and dignified, like the musical tempo largo"}, {"page": "263", "word": "cooks and field hands", "sentence": "She meant the [[cooks and field hands]], the Black workers.", "kor": "요리사들과 들일꾼들", "eng": "Black domestic and farm workers"}, {"page": "263", "word": "settling down", "sentence": "They weren't [[settling down]], calming after the verdict.", "kor": "진정되다/안정을 찾다", "eng": "calming down"}, {"page": "263", "word": "grumbled", "sentence": "Some [[grumbled]], complaining in low voices.", "kor": "투덜거리다", "eng": "complained in a low, discontented way"}, {"page": "263", "word": "hypocrisy", "sentence": "It reeked of [[hypocrisy]], claiming virtue while doing the opposite.", "kor": "위선", "eng": "claiming virtues one does not practice"}, {"page": "263", "word": "irony", "sentence": "There was bitter [[irony]] in it, a gap between word and reality.", "kor": "아이러니/반어", "eng": "a gap between what is said or expected and reality"}, {"page": "263", "word": "reversal", "sentence": "It was a cruel [[reversal]], a turning into the opposite.", "kor": "반전", "eng": "a turning of a situation into its opposite"}, {"page": "263", "word": "compassion", "sentence": "They lacked [[compassion]], the sympathy that moves to help.", "kor": "연민/긍휼", "eng": "deep sympathy that moves one to help"}, {"page": "264", "word": "sulky", "sentence": "Scout looked [[sulky]], silently resentful.", "kor": "부루퉁한", "eng": "silently bad-tempered and resentful"}, {"page": "264", "word": "dissatisfied", "sentence": "Mrs. Merriweather was [[dissatisfied]], not content.", "kor": "불만족스러운", "eng": "not content"}, {"page": "264", "word": "let her go", "sentence": "She'd nearly [[let her go]], dismissed her maid (a euphemism).", "kor": "해고하다", "eng": "(euphemism) dismiss her from her job"}, {"page": "264", "word": "the depression", "sentence": "It was [[the depression]], the Great Depression of the 1930s.", "kor": "경제 대공황", "eng": "the Great Depression of the 1930s"}, {"page": "264", "word": "doesn't stick going down", "sentence": "The excuse [[doesn't stick going down]], troubling no conscience to swallow (idiom).", "kor": "목에 걸리지 않다", "eng": "(idiom) causes no discomfort of conscience to swallow"}, {"page": "264", "word": "stopped (her) cold", "sentence": "Miss Maudie [[stopped her cold]], halting her suddenly.", "kor": "그 자리에서 얼어붙게 하다", "eng": "made her stop suddenly and completely"}, {"page": "264", "word": "tight lines", "sentence": "There were [[tight lines]] round her mouth, tense ones.", "kor": "팽팽한 주름/긴장된 표정선", "eng": "tense lines around the eyes or mouth"}, {"page": "264", "word": "lost the thread of conversation", "sentence": "Scout [[lost the thread of conversation]], losing track of it.", "kor": "대화의 맥락을 놓치다", "eng": "lost track of what was being discussed"}, {"page": "264", "word": "splendidly built", "sentence": "Mrs. Merriweather was [[splendidly built]], impressively solid.", "kor": "체격이 훌륭한", "eng": "having an impressively solid figure"}, {"page": "264", "word": "fresh permanent wave", "sentence": "She had a [[fresh permanent wave]], a new perm.", "kor": "갓 한 파마", "eng": "a newly done perm hairstyle"}, {"page": "264", "word": "ringlets", "sentence": "Her hair fell in [[ringlets]], small spiral curls.", "kor": "고리 모양 곱슬머리", "eng": "small spiral curls of hair"}, {"page": "264", "word": "prefacing", "sentence": "She kept [[prefacing]] her words, leading in with a sound.", "kor": "서두를 떼다", "eng": "introducing speech with a preliminary sound or remark"}, {"page": "264", "word": "sibilant sound", "sentence": "She made a [[sibilant sound]], a hissing 's.'", "kor": "쉬익 하는 치찰음", "eng": "a hissing 's' sound"}, {"page": "264", "word": "fighting a losing battle", "sentence": "Scout was [[fighting a losing battle]], doomed to fail (idiom).", "kor": "승산 없는 싸움을 하다", "eng": "(idiom) struggling at something doomed to fail"}, {"page": "264", "word": "blue in the face", "sentence": "She'd argue [[blue in the face]], till worn out (idiom).", "kor": "지칠 때까지/얼굴이 새파래질 때까지", "eng": "(idiom) to the point of exhaustion from trying"}, {"page": "264", "word": "cognitive dissonance", "sentence": "The ladies felt [[cognitive dissonance]], the discomfort of holding two clashing beliefs at once.", "kor": "인지부조화", "eng": "discomfort from holding contradictory beliefs"}, {"page": "264", "word": "systemic racism", "sentence": "It was [[systemic racism]], prejudice built into the town's very institutions.", "kor": "제도적 인종차별", "eng": "racism built into institutions and systems"}, {"page": "265", "word": "no lady safe in her bed", "sentence": "She claimed [[no lady safe in her bed]], the racist scare that white women were endangered.", "kor": "침대에서도 안전한 숙녀가 없다", "eng": "a racist scare-claim that white women were in danger"}, {"page": "265", "word": "coming to", "sentence": "What was the world [[coming to]], reaching such a state?", "kor": "어떤 지경에 이르다", "eng": "reaching (a bad) state of affairs"}, {"page": "265", "word": "far be it from me", "sentence": "\"[[Far be it from me]] to say,\" she said — I'd never presume (idiom).", "kor": "내가 결코 ~할 생각은 없지만", "eng": "(idiom) I would never presume to..."}, {"page": "265", "word": "read in that field", "sentence": "She wasn't [[read in that field]], not knowledgeable in it.", "kor": "그 분야에 식견이 있는", "eng": "knowledgeable in that subject"}, {"page": "265", "word": "misguided", "sentence": "Atticus was [[misguided]], they said — acting on wrong beliefs.", "kor": "잘못 인도된/그릇된", "eng": "acting on wrong beliefs, though perhaps well-meaning"}, {"page": "265", "word": "stir them up", "sentence": "He'd [[stir them up]], provoke them to discontent.", "kor": "그들을 선동하다", "eng": "provoke them into discontent"}, {"page": "265", "word": "entered that wool of hers", "sentence": "The idea [[entered that wool of hers]] — a racist way of saying it occurred to the maid.", "kor": "그녀의 머릿속에 들어가다 (비하 표현)", "eng": "(racist idiom) occurred to her mind"}, {"page": "265", "word": "a dollar and a quarter", "sentence": "She paid [[a dollar and a quarter]] a week, one dollar twenty-five cents.", "kor": "1달러 25센트", "eng": "one dollar and twenty-five cents (a week's pay)"}, {"page": "265", "word": "brevity", "sentence": "Miss Maudie answered with [[brevity]], shortness of speech.", "kor": "간결함", "eng": "shortness of speech"}, {"page": "265", "word": "icy", "sentence": "Her tone was [[icy]], coldly hostile.", "kor": "얼음처럼 차가운", "eng": "coldly hostile"}, {"page": "265", "word": "engaging (someone) in", "sentence": "She kept [[engaging]] Scout in talk, drawing her into it.", "kor": "~를 끌어들이다", "eng": "drawing someone into (conversation)"}, {"page": "265", "word": "brisk conversation", "sentence": "It was [[brisk conversation]], quick and energetic.", "kor": "활기찬 대화", "eng": "quick, energetic talk"}, {"page": "265", "word": "well on the road", "sentence": "Scout was [[well on the road]] to ladyhood, making good progress.", "kor": "순조롭게 진행 중인", "eng": "making good progress toward"}, {"page": "265", "word": "oppression", "sentence": "They ignored real [[oppression]], unjust cruelty over a group.", "kor": "억압/탄압", "eng": "unjust, cruel use of power over a group"}, {"page": "265", "word": "trope", "sentence": "The 'happy servant' was a [[trope]], a stock literary device.", "kor": "트로프/상투적 장치", "eng": "a recurring literary device or theme"}, {"page": "265", "word": "onomatopoeic", "sentence": "'Buzz' is [[onomatopoeic]], imitating the sound it names.", "kor": "의성어의", "eng": "imitating the sound it describes"}, {"page": "266", "word": "look of pure gratitude", "sentence": "She gave a [[look of pure gratitude]], unmixed thankfulness.", "kor": "순수한 감사의 눈빛", "eng": "an expression of unmixed thankfulness"}, {"page": "266", "word": "sufficiently", "sentence": "She'd recovered [[sufficiently]], to an adequate degree.", "kor": "충분히", "eng": "to an adequate degree"}, {"page": "266", "word": "rocked slowly", "sentence": "The ladies [[rocked slowly]], swaying in their chairs.", "kor": "천천히 흔들의자를 타다", "eng": "swayed gently in rocking chairs"}, {"page": "266", "word": "fanned gently", "sentence": "They [[fanned gently]], waving fans softly.", "kor": "부드럽게 부채질하다", "eng": "waved fans softly"}, {"page": "266", "word": "blood-curdling", "sentence": "It was a [[blood-curdling]] tale, terrifying.", "kor": "소름 끼치는", "eng": "terrifying; chilling the blood"}, {"page": "266", "word": "dreary", "sentence": "The talk grew [[dreary]], dull and depressing.", "kor": "지루한/황량한", "eng": "dull and depressing"}, {"page": "266", "word": "shortly", "sentence": "Miss Maudie answered [[shortly]], curt and brief.", "kor": "퉁명스럽게/짧게", "eng": "curtly; in a brief, abrupt way"}, {"page": "266", "word": "hypocrites", "sentence": "They were [[hypocrites]], preaching what they didn't practise.", "kor": "위선자들", "eng": "people who claim morals they do not practice"}, {"page": "266", "word": "deceit", "sentence": "It was sheer [[deceit]], dishonesty.", "kor": "기만/속임수", "eng": "dishonesty; deception"}, {"page": "266", "word": "plain", "sentence": "It was [[plain]] wrong, simply and downright so.", "kor": "완전히/그저", "eng": "(informal) simply, downright"}, {"page": "266", "word": "born hypocrites", "sentence": "They were [[born hypocrites]], hypocrites by nature.", "kor": "타고난 위선자들", "eng": "hypocrites by nature"}, {"page": "266", "word": "foil", "sentence": "Miss Maudie was a [[foil]], setting off the others by contrast.", "kor": "(돋보이게 하는) 대조 인물", "eng": "a character who highlights another by contrast"}, {"page": "266", "word": "rebuttal", "sentence": "Her words were a [[rebuttal]], proving the claim false.", "kor": "반박", "eng": "a statement proving a claim wrong"}, {"page": "267", "word": "neither of us", "sentence": "[[Neither of us]] spoke, not one of the two.", "kor": "우리 중 누구도 ~아니다", "eng": "not one of the two of us"}, {"page": "267", "word": "catch its breath", "sentence": "The town needed to [[catch its breath]], to pause and recover (idiom).", "kor": "숨을 고르다", "eng": "(idiom) pause to recover"}, {"page": "267", "word": "taking things (as they come)", "sentence": "Atticus was [[taking things]] as they came, accepting without resistance.", "kor": "상황을 (오는 대로) 받아들이다", "eng": "accepting events without resistance"}, {"page": "267", "word": "shut up (in prison)", "sentence": "Tom was [[shut up]] in prison, locked away.", "kor": "갇히다", "eng": "confined; locked away"}, {"page": "267", "word": "leave it at that", "sentence": "She'd [[leave it at that]], say no more (idiom).", "kor": "그쯤에서 그만두다", "eng": "(idiom) say or do no more about it"}, {"page": "267", "word": "black dark", "sentence": "It was [[black dark]], complete blackness.", "kor": "깜깜한 어둠", "eng": "complete darkness"}, {"page": "267", "word": "his face was white", "sentence": "[[His face was white]], pale with shock.", "kor": "얼굴이 창백했다", "eng": "his face was pale (with shock)"}, {"page": "267", "word": "half risen", "sentence": "He stood [[half risen]], partly up from his chair.", "kor": "절반쯤 일어선", "eng": "partly standing up"}, {"page": "267", "word": "exercise period", "sentence": "It was during the [[exercise period]], the prisoners' outdoor time.", "kor": "운동 시간", "eng": "prisoners' scheduled outdoor time"}, {"page": "267", "word": "broke into a blind raving charge", "sentence": "Tom [[broke into a blind raving charge]], running wild without seeing or thinking.", "kor": "눈먼 듯 미친 듯이 내달리다", "eng": "suddenly ran wildly, without seeing or thinking"}, {"page": "267", "word": "fumbling at her apron", "sentence": "Cal stood [[fumbling at her apron]], hurrying clumsily with its strings.", "kor": "앞치마를 허둥지둥 만지작거리며", "eng": "clumsily hurrying with her apron strings"}, {"page": "267", "word": "segregation", "sentence": "It was [[segregation]], the forced separation of races.", "kor": "인종 분리", "eng": "enforced separation of races"}, {"page": "268", "word": "more or less", "sentence": "They shrugged it off [[more or less]], as if one death hardly mattered.", "kor": "대수롭지 않게/한 명쯤 더하든 덜하든", "eng": "approximately; (here) as if it hardly mattered"}, {"page": "268", "word": "the last straw", "sentence": "It was [[the last straw]], the final unbearable blow (idiom).", "kor": "최후의 한계/더는 못 견딜 일", "eng": "(idiom) the final burden that breaks one's endurance"}, {"page": "268", "word": "depends on how you look at it", "sentence": "It [[depends on how you look at it]], changing with your view.", "kor": "어떻게 보느냐에 달렸다", "eng": "it changes according to your perspective"}, {"page": "268", "word": "accumulation", "sentence": "It was an [[accumulation]], a slow piling-up.", "kor": "축적", "eng": "a gradual piling up"}, {"page": "268", "word": "fragility", "sentence": "He saw the [[fragility]] of it, how easily it broke.", "kor": "취약함/연약함", "eng": "the quality of being easily broken"}, {"page": "268", "word": "in truth", "sentence": "[[In truth]], honestly, he'd given up hope.", "kor": "사실대로 말하자면", "eng": "honestly; in fact"}, {"page": "268", "word": "take his own (chances)", "sentence": "Tom chose to [[take his own]] chances, trusting himself instead.", "kor": "자신의 방식대로 (운에) 맡기다", "eng": "rely on his own chances instead"}, {"page": "268", "word": "put her hands to her face", "sentence": "Aunt Alexandra [[put her hands to her face]], covering it.", "kor": "얼굴을 두 손에 묻다", "eng": "covered her face with her hands"}, {"page": "268", "word": "quite still", "sentence": "She sat [[quite still]], completely motionless.", "kor": "아주 가만히", "eng": "completely motionless"}, {"page": "268", "word": "weary", "sentence": "Atticus looked [[weary]], deeply tired.", "kor": "지친/기진맥진한", "eng": "deeply tired"}, {"page": "268", "word": "flat", "sentence": "His voice was [[flat]], toneless.", "kor": "단조로운/무미건조한", "eng": "toneless; without expression"}, {"page": "268", "word": "tears him to pieces", "sentence": "Guilt [[tears him to pieces]], tormenting him inside (idiom).", "kor": "그를 갈가리 찢어놓다/심하게 괴롭히다", "eng": "(idiom) torments him deeply inside"}, {"page": "268", "word": "lose 'em a nickel", "sentence": "It wouldn't [[lose 'em a nickel]], cost them even five cents.", "kor": "단돈 5센트라도 손해 보다", "eng": "cost them even five cents"}, {"page": "268", "word": "wreck his health", "sentence": "It would [[wreck his health]], ruin it.", "kor": "건강을 해치다", "eng": "ruin his health"}, {"page": "268", "word": "paying the highest tribute", "sentence": "The Black community was [[paying the highest tribute]], the greatest honour.", "kor": "최고의 경의를 표하다", "eng": "giving the greatest possible honor"}, {"page": "268", "word": "White Only", "sentence": "Signs read [[White Only]], reserving things for white people.", "kor": "백인 전용", "eng": "a segregation-era sign reserving things for white people"}, {"page": "268", "word": "humility", "sentence": "She showed [[humility]], modest awareness of her limits.", "kor": "겸손", "eng": "modest awareness of one's own limits"}, {"page": "269", "word": "there but for the Lord's kindness am I", "sentence": "\"[[There but for the Lord's kindness am I]]\" — only grace, she felt, set her fate apart from theirs.", "kor": "주님의 자비가 아니었다면 나 또한 저 처지였으리라", "eng": "(idiom) only grace separates my fate from theirs"}, {"page": "269", "word": "crispness", "sentence": "She spoke with [[crispness]], sharp decisiveness.", "kor": "선명함/단호함", "eng": "sharp, brisk decisiveness"}, {"page": "269", "word": "background", "sentence": "True [[background]] meant character, not bloodline — moral substance.", "kor": "근본/배경 (이 소설에서: 도덕적 실체)", "eng": "family standing; (here redefined) moral substance"}, {"page": "269", "word": "left them long enough", "sentence": "She'd [[left them long enough]], stayed away too long.", "kor": "그들을 너무 오래 비워 두었다", "eng": "stayed away from them too long"}, {"page": "269", "word": "smoothed", "sentence": "She [[smoothed]] her dress, pressing it flat.", "kor": "매만지다/펴다", "eng": "pressed flat and neat"}, {"page": "269", "word": "whalebone ridges", "sentence": "She felt the [[whalebone ridges]], the stiff corset stays beneath.", "kor": "고래뼈 지지대 (코르셋 뼈대)", "eng": "the stiff corset stays beneath her dress"}, {"page": "269", "word": "handkerchief", "sentence": "She took a [[handkerchief]], a small cloth for the face.", "kor": "손수건", "eng": "a small cloth for wiping the face"}, {"page": "269", "word": "Do I show it?", "sentence": "\"[[Do I show it?]]\" she asked — does my distress show?", "kor": "내 감정이 티가 나니?", "eng": "can you see my distress?"}, {"page": "269", "word": "not a sign", "sentence": "\"[[Not a sign]],\" Miss Maudie said — no trace at all.", "kor": "전혀 티 안 나", "eng": "no visible trace at all"}, {"page": "269", "word": "grimly", "sentence": "Scout smiled [[grimly]], sternly.", "kor": "엄격하게/단호하게", "eng": "in a stern, unsmiling way"}, {"page": "269", "word": "errand", "sentence": "She went on an [[errand]], a small task.", "kor": "심부름/간단한 용무", "eng": "a short trip for a small task"}, {"page": "269", "word": "dishing out goodies", "sentence": "She helped, [[dishing out goodies]], serving treats.", "kor": "맛있는 것들을 담아 주며", "eng": "serving out treats"}, {"page": "269", "word": "temporary domestic disaster", "sentence": "It was a [[temporary domestic disaster]], a passing household mishap.", "kor": "일시적인 가사 재앙", "eng": "a passing household mishap"}, {"page": "269", "word": "martyred", "sentence": "Tom seemed almost [[martyred]], a victim who had died for a cause.", "kor": "순교한", "eng": "having died (or suffered) for a faith or cause"}, {"page": "269", "word": "best company manners", "sentence": "Scout put on her [[best company manners]], her politest behaviour.", "kor": "최고의 손님맞이 예절", "eng": "one's most polite behavior for guests"}, {"page": "269", "word": "hostile", "sentence": "The world felt [[hostile]], unfriendly.", "kor": "적대적인", "eng": "showing enmity; unfriendly"}, {"page": "269", "word": "resilience", "sentence": "They showed [[resilience]], recovering from hardship.", "kor": "회복력/탄력성", "eng": "the ability to recover from hardship"}, {"page": "269", "word": "stoicism", "sentence": "And [[stoicism]], enduring pain without showing it.", "kor": "극기주의", "eng": "enduring pain without showing feeling"}], "25": [{"page": "270", "word": "set him out", "sentence": "Scout would [[set him out]], put him outside.", "kor": "밖으로 내놓다", "eng": "put him outside"}, {"page": "270", "word": "scooped up", "sentence": "She [[scooped up]] the bug, lifting it in one motion.", "kor": "떠내다/들어 올리다", "eng": "lifted up in one motion"}, {"page": "270", "word": "cot", "sentence": "Jem lay on a [[cot]], a simple portable bed.", "kor": "간이침대", "eng": "a simple portable bed"}, {"page": "270", "word": "not a trace of", "sentence": "There was [[not a trace of]] worry, no sign at all.", "kor": "~의 흔적도 없는", "eng": "with no sign at all of"}, {"page": "270", "word": "back screen porch", "sentence": "They slept on the [[back screen porch]], the screened rear porch.", "kor": "방충망 친 뒷베란다", "eng": "a rear porch enclosed with insect screens"}, {"page": "270", "word": "lightning bugs", "sentence": "[[Lightning bugs]] blinked, fireflies in the dark.", "kor": "반딧불이", "eng": "fireflies"}, {"page": "270", "word": "night crawlers", "sentence": "[[Night crawlers]] came out, big earthworms surfacing at night.", "kor": "밤지렁이", "eng": "large earthworms that surface at night"}, {"page": "270", "word": "beat against the screen", "sentence": "Moths [[beat against the screen]], hitting the insect mesh.", "kor": "방충망에 부딪히다", "eng": "kept hitting the insect screen"}, {"page": "270", "word": "roly-poly", "sentence": "A [[roly-poly]] crawled by, a pill bug that curls into a ball.", "kor": "콩벌레/공벌레", "eng": "a pill bug that rolls into a ball"}, {"page": "270", "word": "reasoned", "sentence": "Scout [[reasoned]] it out, concluding by logic.", "kor": "추론하다/판단하다", "eng": "concluded by logic"}, {"page": "270", "word": "tiny varmint", "sentence": "It was a [[tiny varmint]], a small pest (dialect).", "kor": "작은 해충/벌레", "eng": "(dialect) a small pest animal"}, {"page": "270", "word": "poked", "sentence": "She [[poked]] it, prodding lightly.", "kor": "쿡 찌르다", "eng": "prodded lightly"}, {"page": "270", "word": "unrolled", "sentence": "It [[unrolled]], uncurling itself.", "kor": "몸을 펴다", "eng": "uncurled itself"}, {"page": "270", "word": "end things", "sentence": "She meant to [[end things]], to kill it (a euphemism).", "kor": "상황을 끝내다/죽이다", "eng": "(euphemism) to kill it"}, {"page": "270", "word": "scowling", "sentence": "Jem lay [[scowling]], frowning angrily.", "kor": "얼굴을 찌푸리다", "eng": "frowning angrily"}, {"page": "270", "word": "stage he was going through", "sentence": "It was a [[stage he was going through]], a passing phase.", "kor": "그가 거치는 단계", "eng": "a temporary phase of growing up"}, {"page": "270", "word": "charity", "sentence": "He'd developed a [[charity]] toward creatures, a gentle kindness.", "kor": "자비/관대함", "eng": "kindness and generosity"}, {"page": "271", "word": "mash him", "sentence": "\"Don't [[mash him]],\" he said — crush it (dialect).", "kor": "그를 짓이기다", "eng": "(dialect) crush it"}, {"page": "271", "word": "because they don't bother you", "sentence": "\"[[Because they don't bother you]],\" he said — they do you no harm.", "kor": "너를 괴롭히지 않으니까", "eng": "the reason given: it does you no harm"}, {"page": "271", "word": "reckon", "sentence": "\"I [[reckon]] you're right,\" said Scout — suppose (dialect).", "kor": "~라고 생각하다 (방언)", "eng": "(dialect) suppose, think"}, {"page": "271", "word": "aw dry up", "sentence": "\"[[Aw dry up]],\" she muttered — stop talking (slang).", "kor": "그만 좀 해", "eng": "(slang) stop talking"}, {"page": "271", "word": "drowsily", "sentence": "Jem answered [[drowsily]], sleepily.", "kor": "졸린 듯이", "eng": "sleepily"}, {"page": "271", "word": "microcosm", "sentence": "The bug was a [[microcosm]], a small mirror of the larger world.", "kor": "축소판", "eng": "a small version of something larger"}, {"page": "271", "word": "empathy", "sentence": "Jem had learned [[empathy]], feeling with another being.", "kor": "공감", "eng": "feeling with another being"}, {"page": "271", "word": "innocence", "sentence": "He defended its [[innocence]], its freedom from guilt or harm.", "kor": "무고함/순수", "eng": "freedom from guilt or harm"}, {"page": "271", "word": "out of sight, out of mind", "sentence": "It was [[out of sight, out of mind]], soon forgotten when unseen (idiom).", "kor": "눈에서 멀어지면 마음에서도 멀어진다", "eng": "(idiom) what is unseen is soon forgotten"}, {"page": "271", "word": "wide awake", "sentence": "Scout lay [[wide awake]], fully alert.", "kor": "정신이 말짱한", "eng": "fully awake"}, {"page": "271", "word": "catch a ride", "sentence": "Atticus had to [[catch a ride]], get a lift.", "kor": "차를 얻어 타다", "eng": "get a lift"}, {"page": "271", "word": "cotton wagon", "sentence": "He rode a [[cotton wagon]], one hauling cotton.", "kor": "목화 마차", "eng": "a wagon hauling cotton"}, {"page": "271", "word": "passing motorist", "sentence": "Or a [[passing motorist]], a driver going by.", "kor": "지나가는 운전자", "eng": "a driver going by"}, {"page": "271", "word": "creek", "sentence": "They crossed a [[creek]], a small stream.", "kor": "개울", "eng": "a small stream"}, {"page": "271", "word": "prospect", "sentence": "It was a dull [[prospect]], the thing she looked forward to.", "kor": "전망/예상", "eng": "the thing looked forward to"}, {"page": "271", "word": "dusk", "sentence": "It happened at [[dusk]], the dim light after sunset.", "kor": "황혼/해질녘", "eng": "the dim light after sunset"}, {"page": "271", "word": "tiresome", "sentence": "The wait was [[tiresome]], annoyingly dull.", "kor": "지루한/성가신", "eng": "annoyingly dull"}, {"page": "272", "word": "caught up with", "sentence": "Dill [[caught up with]] Atticus, reaching him.", "kor": "~을 따라잡다", "eng": "reached someone ahead"}, {"page": "272", "word": "pleaded", "sentence": "They'd [[pleaded]] to come, begging earnestly.", "kor": "간청하다", "eng": "begged earnestly"}, {"page": "272", "word": "the dump", "sentence": "They passed [[the dump]], the garbage ground.", "kor": "쓰레기장", "eng": "the garbage dumping ground"}, {"page": "272", "word": "narrow lane", "sentence": "Down a [[narrow lane]], a slim path.", "kor": "좁은 길", "eng": "a slim country path"}, {"page": "272", "word": "Negro cabins", "sentence": "Past the [[Negro cabins]], the homes of the Black settlement.", "kor": "흑인들의 오두막", "eng": "the small homes of the Black settlement"}, {"page": "272", "word": "playing marbles", "sentence": "Children were [[playing marbles]], at the marble game.", "kor": "구슬치기를 하다", "eng": "playing the marble game"}, {"page": "272", "word": "fetch", "sentence": "He went to [[fetch]] Helen, to bring her.", "kor": "데려오다/가져오다", "eng": "go and bring back"}, {"page": "272", "word": "scampered off", "sentence": "A child [[scampered off]], running quickly.", "kor": "재빨리 달려가다", "eng": "ran off quickly"}, {"page": "272", "word": "stiff pigtails", "sentence": "She had [[stiff pigtails]], tightly braided hair sticking out.", "kor": "뻣뻣하게 땋은 머리", "eng": "tightly braided hair sticking out"}, {"page": "272", "word": "grinned from ear to ear", "sentence": "She [[grinned from ear to ear]], smiling very widely (idiom).", "kor": "입이 귀에 걸리도록 웃다", "eng": "(idiom) smiled very widely"}, {"page": "272", "word": "eased", "sentence": "Atticus [[eased]] the news to her, breaking it gently.", "kor": "조심스럽게 옮기다", "eng": "moved gently and carefully"}, {"page": "272", "word": "trotting", "sentence": "She came [[trotting]], at a quick light pace.", "kor": "총총걸음으로 걷다", "eng": "moving at a quick, light pace"}, {"page": "272", "word": "fell down in the dirt", "sentence": "Helen [[fell down in the dirt]], collapsing to the ground.", "kor": "흙바닥에 쓰러지다", "eng": "collapsed onto the ground"}, {"page": "272", "word": "stepped on (like an ant)", "sentence": "She dropped as if [[stepped on]] like an ant, Dill said — crushed underfoot.", "kor": "(개미처럼) 짓밟다", "eng": "crushed underfoot — Dill's simile for Helen's collapse"}, {"page": "272", "word": "half carried, half walked", "sentence": "Atticus [[half carried, half walked]] her, supporting her along.", "kor": "부축하며 걷다", "eng": "supported her partly carrying her"}, {"page": "272", "word": "hollered", "sentence": "The children [[hollered]], shouting.", "kor": "소리치다", "eng": "shouted"}, {"page": "273", "word": "spread through the county", "sentence": "The news [[spread through the county]], crossing the whole county.", "kor": "군 전체에 퍼지다", "eng": "traveled across the whole county"}, {"page": "273", "word": "typical", "sentence": "Folks called it [[typical]], just what they'd expect — a racist dismissal.", "kor": "전형적인", "eng": "just what you would expect (here: a racist dismissal)"}, {"page": "273", "word": "cut and run", "sentence": "He'd [[cut and run]], fleeing to escape (idiom).", "kor": "도망치다", "eng": "(idiom) flee to escape trouble"}, {"page": "273", "word": "mentality", "sentence": "It was their [[mentality]], a fixed way of thinking.", "kor": "사고방식", "eng": "a fixed way of thinking"}, {"page": "273", "word": "run blind", "sentence": "He'd [[run blind]], without thinking or seeing.", "kor": "앞뒤 안 가리고 달리다", "eng": "run without thinking or seeing"}, {"page": "273", "word": "scot free", "sentence": "No one would go [[scot free]], unpunished (idiom).", "kor": "아무 벌 없이", "eng": "(idiom) completely unpunished"}, {"page": "273", "word": "easy come, easy go", "sentence": "Life was [[easy come, easy go]] to them, carelessly held (idiom).", "kor": "될 대로 되라는 식", "eng": "(idiom) carelessly gained, carelessly lost"}, {"page": "273", "word": "legally married", "sentence": "Tom was [[legally married]], wed under the law.", "kor": "법적으로 결혼한", "eng": "married under the law"}, {"page": "273", "word": "kept himself clean", "sentence": "He'd [[kept himself clean]], stayed out of trouble."